52 const char* OpcodeToString(Opcode opcode) {
53 #define DEF_NAME(Name) #Name,
54  static constexpr const char* const names[] = {NODE_BASE_LIST(DEF_NAME)};
55 #undef DEF_NAME
56  return names[static_cast<int>(opcode)];
57 }

65 // Prevent people from accidentally using kScratchRegister here and having their
66 // code break in arm64.
67 [[maybe_unused]] struct Do_not_use_kScratchRegister_in_arch_independent_code {
68 } kScratchRegister;
69 [[maybe_unused]] struct
70  Do_not_use_kScratchDoubleRegister_in_arch_independent_code {
71 } kScratchDoubleRegister;
72 static_assert(!std::is_same_v<decltype(kScratchRegister), Register>);
73 static_assert(
74  !std::is_same_v<decltype(kScratchDoubleRegister), DoubleRegister>);

90 void NodeBase::CheckCanOverwriteWith(Opcode new_opcode,
91  OpProperties new_properties) {
92  if (new_opcode == Opcode::kDead) return;
93 
94  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_properties.can_eager_deopt(),
95  properties().can_eager_deopt());
96  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_properties.can_lazy_deopt(),
97  properties().can_lazy_deopt());
98  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_properties.needs_register_snapshot(),
99  properties().needs_register_snapshot());
100 
101  int old_input_count = input_count();
102  size_t old_sizeof = -1;
103  switch (opcode()) {
104 #define CASE(op) \
105  case Opcode::k##op: \
106  old_sizeof = sizeof(op); \
107  break;
108  NODE_BASE_LIST(CASE);
109 #undef CASE
110  }
111 
112  switch (new_opcode) {
113 #define CASE(op) \
114  case Opcode::k##op: { \
115  DCHECK_EQ(old_input_count, StaticInputCount(static_cast<op*>(this))); \
116  DCHECK_LE(sizeof(op), old_sizeof); \
117  break; \
118  }
119  NODE_BASE_LIST(CASE)
120 #undef CASE
121  }
122 }

124 #endif // DEBUG

126 bool Phi::is_loop_phi() const { return merge_state()->is_loop(); }
127 
128 bool Phi::is_unmerged_loop_phi() const {
129  DCHECK(is_loop_phi());
130  return merge_state()->is_unmerged_loop();
131 }
132 
133 void Phi::RecordUseReprHint(UseRepresentationSet repr_mask) {
134  if (is_loop_phi() && is_unmerged_loop_phi()) {
135  same_loop_uses_repr_hint_.Add(repr_mask);
136  }
137 
138  if (!repr_mask.is_subset_of(uses_repr_hint_)) {
139  uses_repr_hint_.Add(repr_mask);
140 
141  // Propagate in inputs, ignoring unbounded loop backedges.
142  int bound_inputs = input_count();
143  if (merge_state()->is_unmerged_loop()) --bound_inputs;
144 
145  for (int i = 0; i < bound_inputs; i++) {
146  if (Phi* phi_input = input(i).node()->TryCast<Phi>()) {
147  phi_input->RecordUseReprHint(repr_mask);
148  }
149  }
150  }
151 }
152 
153 void Phi::SetUseRequires31BitValue() {
154  if (uses_require_31_bit_value()) return;
155  set_uses_require_31_bit_value();
156  auto inputs =
157  is_loop_phi() ? merge_state_->predecessors_so_far() : input_count();
158  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < inputs; ++i) {
159  ValueNode* input_node = input(i).node();
160  DCHECK(input_node);
161  if (auto phi = input_node->TryCast<Phi>()) {
162  phi->SetUseRequires31BitValue();
163  }
164  }
165 }

176 bool IsStoreToNonEscapedObject(const NodeBase* node) {
177  if (CanBeStoreToNonEscapedObject(node->opcode())) {
178  DCHECK_GT(node->input_count(), 0);
179  if (InlinedAllocation* alloc =
180  node->input(0).node()->template TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
181  return alloc->HasBeenAnalysed() && alloc->HasBeenElided();
182  }
183  }
184  return false;
185 }

187 void PrintInputs(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
188  const NodeBase* node) {
189  if (!node->has_inputs()) return;
190 
191  os << " [";
192  for (int i = 0; i < node->input_count(); i++) {
193  if (i != 0) os << ", ";
194  graph_labeller->PrintInput(os, node->input(i));
195  }
196  os << "]";
197 }
198 
199 void PrintResult(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
200  const NodeBase* node) {}
201 
202 void PrintResult(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
203  const ValueNode* node) {
204  os << " → " << node->result().operand();
205  if (node->result().operand().IsAllocated() && node->is_spilled() &&
206  node->spill_slot() != node->result().operand()) {
207  os << " (spilled: " << node->spill_slot() << ")";
208  }
209  if (node->has_valid_live_range()) {
210  os << ", live range: [" << node->live_range().start << "-"
211  << node->live_range().end << "]";
212  }
213  if (!node->has_id()) {
214  os << ", " << node->use_count() << " uses";
215  if (const InlinedAllocation* alloc = node->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
216  os << " (" << alloc->non_escaping_use_count() << " non escaping uses)";
217  if (alloc->HasBeenAnalysed() && alloc->HasBeenElided()) {
218  os << " 🪦";
219  }
220  } else if (!node->is_used()) {
221  if (node->opcode() != Opcode::kAllocationBlock &&
222  node->properties().is_required_when_unused()) {
223  os << ", but required";
224  } else {
225  os << " 🪦";
226  }
227  }
228  }
229 }
230 
231 void PrintTargets(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
232  const NodeBase* node) {}
233 
234 void PrintTargets(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
235  const UnconditionalControlNode* node) {
236  os << " b" << node->target()->id();
237 }
238 
239 void PrintTargets(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
240  const BranchControlNode* node) {
241  os << " b" << node->if_true()->id() << " b" << node->if_false()->id();
242 }
243 
244 void PrintTargets(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
245  const Switch* node) {
246  for (int i = 0; i < node->size(); i++) {
247  const BasicBlockRef& target = node->Cast<Switch>()->targets()[i];
248  os << " b" << target.block_ptr()->id();
249  }
250  if (node->Cast<Switch>()->has_fallthrough()) {
251  BasicBlock* fallthrough_target = node->Cast<Switch>()->fallthrough();
252  os << " b" << fallthrough_target->id();
253  }
254 }

256 class MaybeUnparkForPrint {
257  public:
258  MaybeUnparkForPrint() {
259  LocalHeap* local_heap = LocalHeap::Current();
260  if (!local_heap) {
261  local_heap = Isolate::Current()->main_thread_local_heap();
262  }
263  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(local_heap);
264  if (local_heap->IsParked()) {
265  scope_.emplace(local_heap);
266  }
267  }
268 
269  private:
270  std::optional<UnparkedScope> scope_;
271 };
272 
273 template <typename NodeT>
274 void PrintImpl(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
275  const NodeT* node, bool skip_targets) {
276  MaybeUnparkForPrint unpark;
277  os << node->opcode();
278  node->PrintParams(os, graph_labeller);
279  PrintInputs(os, graph_labeller, node);
280  PrintResult(os, graph_labeller, node);
281  if (IsStoreToNonEscapedObject(node)) {
282  os << " 🪦";
283  }
284  if (!skip_targets) {
285  PrintTargets(os, graph_labeller, node);
286  }
287 }

289 bool RootToBoolean(RootIndex index) {
290  switch (index) {
291  case RootIndex::kFalseValue:
292  case RootIndex::kNullValue:
293  case RootIndex::kUndefinedValue:
294  case RootIndex::kNanValue:
295  case RootIndex::kUndefinedNanValue:
296  case RootIndex::kHoleNanValue:
297  case RootIndex::kMinusZeroValue:
298  case RootIndex::kempty_string:
299 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
300  case RootIndex::kWasmNull:
301 #endif
302  return false;
303  default:
304  return true;
305  }
306 }
307 
308 #ifdef DEBUG
309 // For all RO roots, check that RootToBoolean returns the same value as
310 // BooleanValue on that root.
311 bool CheckToBooleanOnAllRoots(LocalIsolate* local_isolate) {
312  ReadOnlyRoots roots(local_isolate);
313  // Use the READ_ONLY_ROOT_LIST macro list rather than a for loop to get nicer
314  // error messages if there is a failure.
315 #define DO_CHECK(type, name, CamelName) \
316  /* Ignore 'undefined' roots that are not the undefined value itself. */ \
317  if (roots.name() != roots.undefined_value() || \
318  RootIndex::k##CamelName == RootIndex::kUndefinedValue) { \
319  DCHECK_EQ(Object::BooleanValue(roots.name(), local_isolate), \
320  RootToBoolean(RootIndex::k##CamelName)); \
321  }
322  READ_ONLY_ROOT_LIST(DO_CHECK)
323 #undef DO_CHECK
324  return true;
325 }
326 #endif

341 void DeoptInfo::InitializeInputLocations(Zone* zone, size_t count) {
342  DCHECK_NULL(input_locations_);
343  input_locations_ = zone->AllocateArray<InputLocation>(count);
344  // Initialise locations so that they correctly don't have a next use id.
345  for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
346  new (&input_locations_[i]) InputLocation();
347  }
348 #ifdef DEBUG
349  input_location_count_ = count;
350 #endif // DEBUG
351 }

353 bool RootConstant::ToBoolean(LocalIsolate* local_isolate) const {
354 #ifdef DEBUG
355  // (Ab)use static locals to call CheckToBooleanOnAllRoots once, on first
356  // call to this function.
357  static bool check_once = CheckToBooleanOnAllRoots(local_isolate);
358  DCHECK(check_once);
359 #endif
360  // ToBoolean is only supported for RO roots.
361  DCHECK(RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index_));
362  return RootToBoolean(index_);
363 }

365 bool FromConstantToBool(LocalIsolate* local_isolate, ValueNode* node) {
366  DCHECK(IsConstantNode(node->opcode()));
367  switch (node->opcode()) {
368 #define CASE(Name) \
369  case Opcode::k##Name: { \
370  return node->Cast<Name>()->ToBoolean(local_isolate); \
371  }
372  CONSTANT_VALUE_NODE_LIST(CASE)
373 #undef CASE
374  default:
375  UNREACHABLE();
376  }
377 }

388 bool LazyDeoptInfo::IsResultRegister(interpreter::Register reg) const {
389  if (top_frame().type() == DeoptFrame::FrameType::kConstructInvokeStubFrame) {
390  return reg == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator();
391  }
392  if (V8_LIKELY(result_size() == 1)) {
393  return reg == result_location_;
394  }
395  if (result_size() == 0) {
396  return false;
397  }
398  DCHECK_EQ(result_size(), 2);
399  return reg == result_location_ ||
400  reg == interpreter::Register(result_location_.index() + 1);
401 }
402 
403 bool LazyDeoptInfo::InReturnValues(interpreter::Register reg,
404  interpreter::Register result_location,
405  int result_size) {
406  if (result_size == 0 || !result_location.is_valid()) {
407  return false;
408  }
409  return base::IsInRange(reg.index(), result_location.index(),
410  result_location.index() + result_size - 1);
411 }
412 
413 int InterpretedDeoptFrame::ComputeReturnOffset(
414  interpreter::Register result_location, int result_size) const {
415  // Return offsets are counted from the end of the translation frame,
416  // which is the array [parameters..., locals..., accumulator]. Since
417  // it's the end, we don't need to worry about earlier frames.
418  if (result_location == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
419  return 0;
420  } else if (result_location.is_parameter()) {
421  // This is slightly tricky to reason about because of zero indexing
422  // and fence post errors. As an example, consider a frame with 2
423  // locals and 2 parameters, where we want argument index 1 -- looking
424  // at the array in reverse order we have:
425  // [acc, r1, r0, a1, a0]
426  // ^
427  // and this calculation gives, correctly:
428  // 2 + 2 - 1 = 3
429  return unit().register_count() + unit().parameter_count() -
430  result_location.ToParameterIndex();
431  } else {
432  return unit().register_count() - result_location.index();
433  }
434 }
435 
436 const InterpretedDeoptFrame& LazyDeoptInfo::GetFrameForExceptionHandler(
437  const ExceptionHandlerInfo* handler_info) {
438  const DeoptFrame* target_frame = &top_frame();
439  for (int i = 0;; i++) {
440  while (target_frame->type() != DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInterpretedFrame) {
441  target_frame = target_frame->parent();
442  }
443  if (i == handler_info->depth()) break;
444  target_frame = target_frame->parent();
445  }
446  return target_frame->as_interpreted();
447 }

449 void NodeBase::Print(std::ostream& os, MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller,
450  bool skip_targets) const {

453  case Opcode::k##Name: \
454  return PrintImpl(os, graph_labeller, this->Cast<Name>(), skip_targets);
455  NODE_BASE_LIST(V)
456 #undef V
457  }
458  UNREACHABLE();
459 }

467 void ValueNode::SetHint(compiler::InstructionOperand hint) {
468  if (!hint_.IsInvalid()) return;
469  hint_ = hint;
470  if (result_.operand().IsUnallocated()) {
471  auto operand = compiler::UnallocatedOperand::cast(result_.operand());
472  if (operand.HasSameAsInputPolicy()) {
473  input(operand.input_index()).node()->SetHint(hint);
474  }
475  }
476  if (this->Is<Phi>()) {
477  for (Input& input : *this) {
478  if (input.node()->has_id() && input.node()->id() < this->id()) {
479  input.node()->SetHint(hint);
480  }
481  }
482  }
483 }

485 void ValueNode::SetNoSpill() {
486  DCHECK(!IsConstantNode(opcode()));
487 #ifdef DEBUG
488  state_ = kSpill;
489 #endif // DEBUG
490  spill_ = compiler::InstructionOperand();
491 }

493 void ValueNode::SetConstantLocation() {
494  DCHECK(IsConstantNode(opcode()));
495 #ifdef DEBUG
496  state_ = kSpill;
497 #endif // DEBUG
498  spill_ = compiler::ConstantOperand(
499  compiler::UnallocatedOperand::cast(result().operand())
500  .virtual_register());
501 }

503 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef ValueNode::TryGetConstant(
504  compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker) {
505  if (Constant* c = TryCast<Constant>()) {
506  return c->object();
507  }
508  if (RootConstant* c = TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
509  return MakeRef(broker, broker->local_isolate()->root_handle(c->index()))
510  .AsHeapObject();
511  }
512  return {};
513 }
514 
515 NodeType ValueNode::GetStaticType(compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker) {
516  switch (properties().value_representation()) {
517  case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
518  case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
519  case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
520  case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
521  return NodeType::kNumber;
522  case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
523  return NodeType::kNumberOrOddball;
524  case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
525  break;
526  }
527  switch (opcode()) {
528  case Opcode::kPhi:
529  return Cast<Phi>()->type();
530  case Opcode::kCheckedSmiTagInt32:
531  case Opcode::kCheckedSmiTagUint32:
532  case Opcode::kCheckedSmiTagIntPtr:
533  case Opcode::kCheckedSmiTagFloat64:
534  case Opcode::kUnsafeSmiTagInt32:
535  case Opcode::kUnsafeSmiTagUint32:
536  case Opcode::kUnsafeSmiTagIntPtr:
537  case Opcode::kSmiConstant:
538  return NodeType::kSmi;
539  case Opcode::kInt32ToNumber:
540  case Opcode::kUint32ToNumber:
541  case Opcode::kIntPtrToNumber:
542  case Opcode::kFloat64ToTagged:
543  return NodeType::kNumber;
544  case Opcode::kHoleyFloat64ToTagged:
545  return NodeType::kNumberOrOddball;
546  case Opcode::kAllocationBlock:
547  case Opcode::kInlinedAllocation: {
548  auto obj = Cast<InlinedAllocation>()->object();
549  if (obj->has_static_map()) {
550  return StaticTypeForMap(obj->map(), broker);
551  } else {
552  switch (obj->type()) {
553  case VirtualObject::kConsString:
554  return NodeType::kString;
555  case VirtualObject::kDefault:
556  case VirtualObject::kHeapNumber:
557  case VirtualObject::kFixedDoubleArray:
558  UNREACHABLE();
559  }
560  }
561  }
562  case Opcode::kRootConstant: {
563  RootConstant* constant = Cast<RootConstant>();
564  switch (constant->index()) {
565  case RootIndex::kTrueValue:
566  case RootIndex::kFalseValue:
567  return NodeType::kBoolean;
568  case RootIndex::kUndefinedValue:
569  case RootIndex::kNullValue:
570  return NodeType::kOddball;
571  default:
572  break;
573  }
574  [[fallthrough]];
575  }
576  case Opcode::kConstant: {
577  compiler::HeapObjectRef ref = TryGetConstant(broker).value();
578  return StaticTypeForConstant(broker, ref);
579  }
580  case Opcode::kToNumberOrNumeric:
581  if (Cast<ToNumberOrNumeric>()->mode() == Object::Conversion::kToNumber) {
582  return NodeType::kNumber;
583  }
584  // TODO(verwaest): Check what we need here.
585  return NodeType::kUnknown;
586  case Opcode::kBuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt:
587  case Opcode::kBuiltinSeqOneByteStringCharCodeAt:
588  return NodeType::kNumber;
589  case Opcode::kToString:
590  case Opcode::kNumberToString:
591  case Opcode::kUnwrapStringWrapper:
592  case Opcode::kStringAt:
593  case Opcode::kStringConcat:
594  case Opcode::kBuiltinStringFromCharCode:
595  return NodeType::kString;
596  case Opcode::kCheckedInternalizedString:
597  return NodeType::kInternalizedString;
598  case Opcode::kSeqOneByteStringAt:
599  // Seq one-byte StringAt will always return an internalized string from
600  // the single character roots.
601  return NodeType::kROSeqInternalizedOneByteString;
602  case Opcode::kToObject:
603  case Opcode::kCreateObjectLiteral:
604  case Opcode::kCreateShallowObjectLiteral:
605  return NodeType::kJSReceiver;
606  case Opcode::kCreateArrayLiteral:
607  case Opcode::kCreateShallowArrayLiteral:
608  return NodeType::kJSArray;
609  case Opcode::kToName:
610  return NodeType::kName;
611  case Opcode::kFastCreateClosure:
612  case Opcode::kCreateClosure:
613  return NodeType::kJSFunction;
614  case Opcode::kInt32Compare:
615  case Opcode::kFloat64Compare:
616  case Opcode::kGenericEqual:
617  case Opcode::kGenericStrictEqual:
618  case Opcode::kGenericLessThan:
619  case Opcode::kGenericLessThanOrEqual:
620  case Opcode::kGenericGreaterThan:
621  case Opcode::kGenericGreaterThanOrEqual:
622  case Opcode::kLogicalNot:
623  case Opcode::kStringEqual:
624  case Opcode::kTaggedEqual:
625  case Opcode::kTaggedNotEqual:
626  case Opcode::kTestInstanceOf:
627  case Opcode::kTestTypeOf:
628  case Opcode::kTestUndetectable:
629  case Opcode::kToBoolean:
630  case Opcode::kToBooleanLogicalNot:
631  case Opcode::kIntPtrToBoolean:
632  case Opcode::kSetPrototypeHas:
633  return NodeType::kBoolean;
634  case Opcode::kCreateFunctionContext:
635  return NodeType::kContext;
636  case Opcode::kCallRuntime:
637  switch (Cast<CallRuntime>()->function_id()) {
638  case Runtime::kPushBlockContext:
639  case Runtime::kPushCatchContext:
640  case Runtime::kNewFunctionContext:
641  return NodeType::kContext;
642  default:
643  return NodeType::kUnknown;
644  }
645  UNREACHABLE();
646  // Not value nodes:
647 #define GENERATE_CASE(Name) case Opcode::k##Name:

839 
840 ValueRepresentation ToValueRepresentation(MachineType type) {
841  switch (type.representation()) {
842  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
843  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned:
844  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer:
845  return ValueRepresentation::kTagged;
846  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
847  return ValueRepresentation::kFloat64;
848  case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
849  DCHECK_EQ(kSystemPointerSize, 8);
850  return ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr;
851  default:
852  return ValueRepresentation::kInt32;
853  }
854 }
855 
856 void CheckValueInputIs(const NodeBase* node, int i,
857  ValueRepresentation expected,
858  MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller) {
859  ValueNode* input = node->input(i).node();
860  DCHECK(!input->Is<Identity>());
861  ValueRepresentation got = input->properties().value_representation();
862  // Allow Float64 values to be inputs when HoleyFloat64 is expected.
863  bool valid =
864  (got == expected) || (got == ValueRepresentation::kFloat64 &&
865  expected == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64);
866  if (!valid) {
867  std::ostringstream str;
868  str << "Type representation error: node ";
869  if (graph_labeller) {
870  str << "#" << graph_labeller->NodeId(node) << " : ";
871  }
872  str << node->opcode() << " (input @" << i << " = " << input->opcode()
873  << ") type " << got << " is not " << expected;
874  FATAL("%s", str.str().c_str());
875  }
876 }
877 
878 void CheckValueInputIs(const NodeBase* node, int i, Opcode expected,
879  MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller) {
880  ValueNode* input = node->input(i).node();
881  Opcode got = input->opcode();
882  if (got != expected) {
883  std::ostringstream str;
884  str << "Opcode error: node ";
885  if (graph_labeller) {
886  str << "#" << graph_labeller->NodeId(node) << " : ";
887  }
888  str << node->opcode() << " (input @" << i << " = " << input->opcode()
889  << ") opcode " << got << " is not " << expected;
890  FATAL("%s", str.str().c_str());
891  }
892 }
893 
894 void GeneratorStore::VerifyInputs(MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller) const {
895  for (int i = 0; i < input_count(); i++) {
896  CheckValueInputIs(this, i, ValueRepresentation::kTagged, graph_labeller);
897  }
898 }
899 
900 void Phi::VerifyInputs(MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller) const {
901  switch (value_representation()) {
902 #define CASE_REPR(repr) \
903  case ValueRepresentation::k##repr: \
904  for (int i = 0; i < input_count(); i++) { \
905  CheckValueInputIs(this, i, ValueRepresentation::k##repr, \
906  graph_labeller); \
907  } \
908  break;
909 
910  CASE_REPR(Tagged)
911  CASE_REPR(Int32)
912  CASE_REPR(Uint32)
913  CASE_REPR(Float64)
914  CASE_REPR(HoleyFloat64)
915 #undef CASE_REPR
916  case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
917  UNREACHABLE();
918  }
919 }

1052 void CallBuiltin::VerifyInputs(MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller) const {
1053  auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
1054  int count = input_count();
1055  // Verify context.
1056  if (descriptor.HasContextParameter()) {
1057  CheckValueInputIs(this, count - 1, ValueRepresentation::kTagged,
1058  graph_labeller);
1059  count--;
1060  }
1061 
1062 // {all_input_count} includes the feedback slot and vector.
1063 #ifdef DEBUG
1064  int all_input_count = count + (has_feedback() ? 2 : 0);
1065  if (descriptor.AllowVarArgs()) {
1066  DCHECK_GE(all_input_count, descriptor.GetParameterCount());
1067  } else {
1068  DCHECK_EQ(all_input_count, descriptor.GetParameterCount());
1069  }
1070 #endif
1071  int i = 0;
1072  // Check the rest of inputs.
1073  for (; i < count; ++i) {
1074  MachineType type = i < descriptor.GetParameterCount()
1075  ? descriptor.GetParameterType(i)
1076  : MachineType::AnyTagged();
1077  CheckValueInputIs(this, i, ToValueRepresentation(type), graph_labeller);
1078  }
1079 }
1080 
1081 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
1082 void CallBuiltin::MarkTaggedInputsAsDecompressing() {
1083  auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
1084  int count = input_count();
1085  // Set context.
1086  if (descriptor.HasContextParameter()) {
1087  input(count - 1).node()->SetTaggedResultNeedsDecompress();
1088  count--;
1089  }
1090  int i = 0;
1091  // Set the rest of the tagged inputs.
1092  for (; i < count; ++i) {
1093  MachineType type = i < descriptor.GetParameterCount()
1094  ? descriptor.GetParameterType(i)
1095  : MachineType::AnyTagged();
1096  if (type.IsTagged() && !type.IsTaggedSigned()) {
1097  input(i).node()->SetTaggedResultNeedsDecompress();
1098  }
1099  }
1100 }
1101 #endif

1131 void StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier::VerifyInputs(
1132  MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller) const {
1133  Base::VerifyInputs(graph_labeller);
1134  if (auto host_alloc =
1135  input(kObjectIndex).node()->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
1136  if (input(kValueIndex).node()->Is<InlinedAllocation>()) {
1137  CHECK_EQ(host_alloc->allocation_block()->allocation_type(),
1138  AllocationType::kYoung);

1150 AllocationBlock* InlinedAllocation::allocation_block() {
1151  return allocation_block_input().node()->Cast<AllocationBlock>();
1152 }
1153 
1154 void AllocationBlock::TryPretenure() {
1155  if (allocation_type_ == AllocationType::kOld) {
1156  return;
1157  }
1158  if (elided_write_barriers_depend_on_type()) {
1159  return;
1160  }
1161  allocation_type_ = AllocationType::kOld;
1162  for (auto alloc : allocation_list_) {
1163  alloc->object()->ForEachInput(
1164  [&](ValueNode* value) { TryPretenure(value); });
1165  }
1166 }
1167 
1168 void AllocationBlock::TryPretenure(ValueNode* value) {
1169  DCHECK(v8_flags.maglev_pretenure_store_values);
1170  DCHECK_EQ(allocation_type_, AllocationType::kOld);
1171 
1172  if (elided_write_barriers_depend_on_type()) {
1173  return;
1174  }
1175 
1176  if (IsConstantNode(value->opcode())) return;
1177  if (auto next_alloc = value->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
1178  next_alloc->allocation_block()->TryPretenure();
1179  } else if (auto phi = value->TryCast<Phi>()) {
1180  if (!phi->is_loop_phi() || !phi->is_unmerged_loop_phi()) {
1181  for (int i = 0; i < phi->input_count(); ++i) {
1182  auto phi_input = phi->input(i).node();
1183  if (auto phi_alloc = phi_input->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
1184  phi_alloc->allocation_block()->TryPretenure();
1185  }
1186  }
1187  }
1188  }
1189 }

1195 DirectHandle<Object> ValueNode::Reify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
1196  switch (opcode()) {
1197 #define V(Name) \
1198  case Opcode::k##Name: \
1199  return this->Cast<Name>()->DoReify(isolate);
1200  CONSTANT_VALUE_NODE_LIST(V)
1201 #undef V
1202  default:
1203  UNREACHABLE();
1204  }
1205 }

1208  return direct_handle(value_, isolate);
1209 }

1217 }

1240 Handle<Object> RootConstant::DoReify(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {

1246 bool FromConstantToBool(MaglevAssembler* masm, ValueNode* node) {

1248  // actually want here, but it's all we have, and it happens to work because

1258 namespace {
1259 template <typename NodeT>
1260 void LoadToRegisterHelper(NodeT* node, MaglevAssembler* masm, Register reg) {
1261  if constexpr (!IsDoubleRepresentation(
1262  NodeT::kProperties.value_representation())) {
1263  return node->DoLoadToRegister(masm, reg);
1264  } else {
1265  UNREACHABLE();
1266  }
1267 }
1268 template <typename NodeT>
1269 void LoadToRegisterHelper(NodeT* node, MaglevAssembler* masm,
1270  DoubleRegister reg) {
1271  if constexpr (IsDoubleRepresentation(
1272  NodeT::kProperties.value_representation())) {
1273  return node->DoLoadToRegister(masm, reg);
1274  } else {
1275  UNREACHABLE();
1276  }
1277 }
1278 } // namespace

1280 void ValueNode::LoadToRegister(MaglevAssembler* masm, Register reg) {
1281  switch (opcode()) {
1282 #define V(Name) \
1283  case Opcode::k##Name: \
1284  return LoadToRegisterHelper(this->Cast<Name>(), masm, reg);
1285  VALUE_NODE_LIST(V)
1286 #undef V
1287  default:
1288  UNREACHABLE();
1289  }
1290 }
1291 void ValueNode::LoadToRegister(MaglevAssembler* masm, DoubleRegister reg) {
1292  switch (opcode()) {
1293 #define V(Name) \
1294  case Opcode::k##Name: \
1295  return LoadToRegisterHelper(this->Cast<Name>(), masm, reg);
1296  VALUE_NODE_LIST(V)
1297 #undef V
1298  default:
1299  UNREACHABLE();
1300  }
1301 }

1433 int FunctionEntryStackCheck::MaxCallStackArgs() const { return 0; }
1434 void FunctionEntryStackCheck::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1435  set_temporaries_needed(2);
1436  // kReturnRegister0 should not be one of the available temporary registers.
1437  RequireSpecificTemporary(kReturnRegister0);
1438 }
1439 void FunctionEntryStackCheck::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1440  const ProcessingState& state) {
1441  // Stack check. This folds the checks for both the interrupt stack limit
1442  // check and the real stack limit into one by just checking for the
1443  // interrupt limit. The interrupt limit is either equal to the real
1444  // stack limit or tighter. By ensuring we have space until that limit
1445  // after building the frame we can quickly precheck both at once.
1446  const int stack_check_offset = masm->code_gen_state()->stack_check_offset();
1447  // Only NewTarget can be live at this point.
1448  DCHECK_LE(register_snapshot().live_registers.Count(), 1);
1449  Builtin builtin =
1450  register_snapshot().live_tagged_registers.has(
1451  kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister)
1452  ? Builtin::kMaglevFunctionEntryStackCheck_WithNewTarget
1453  : Builtin::kMaglevFunctionEntryStackCheck_WithoutNewTarget;
1454  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
1455  Condition cond = __ FunctionEntryStackCheck(stack_check_offset);
1456  if (masm->isolate()->is_short_builtin_calls_enabled()) {
1457  __ JumpIf(cond, *done, Label::kNear);
1458  __ Move(kReturnRegister0, Smi::FromInt(stack_check_offset));
1459  __ MacroAssembler::CallBuiltin(builtin);
1460  masm->DefineLazyDeoptPoint(lazy_deopt_info());
1461  } else {
1462  __ JumpToDeferredIf(
1463  NegateCondition(cond),
1464  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, ZoneLabelRef done,
1465  FunctionEntryStackCheck* node, Builtin builtin,
1466  int stack_check_offset) {
1467  __ Move(kReturnRegister0, Smi::FromInt(stack_check_offset));
1468  __ MacroAssembler::CallBuiltin(builtin);
1469  masm->DefineLazyDeoptPoint(node->lazy_deopt_info());
1470  __ Jump(*done);
1471  },
1472  done, this, builtin, stack_check_offset);
1473  }
1474  __ bind(*done);
1475 }

1485 void GetSecondReturnedValue::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1486  DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister1);
1487 }
1488 void GetSecondReturnedValue::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1489  const ProcessingState& state) {
1490  // No-op. This is just a hack that binds kReturnRegister1 to a value node.
1491  // kReturnRegister1 is guaranteed to be free in the register allocator, since
1492  // previous node in the basic block is a call.
1493 #ifdef DEBUG
1494  // Check if the previous node is call.
1495  Node* previous = nullptr;
1496  for (Node* node : state.block()->nodes()) {
1497  if (node == this) {
1498  break;
1499  }
1500  previous = node;
1501  }
1502  DCHECK_NE(previous, nullptr);
1503  DCHECK(previous->properties().is_call());
1504 #endif // DEBUG
1505 }

1512 void Phi::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1513  for (Input& input : *this) {
1514  UseAny(input);
1515  }
1516 
1517  // We have to pass a policy for the result, but it is ignored during register
1518  // allocation. See StraightForwardRegisterAllocator::AllocateRegisters which
1519  // has special handling for Phis.
1520  static const compiler::UnallocatedOperand::ExtendedPolicy kIgnoredPolicy =
1521  compiler::UnallocatedOperand::REGISTER_OR_SLOT_OR_CONSTANT;
1522 
1523  result().SetUnallocated(kIgnoredPolicy, kNoVreg);
1524 }

1528 void ArgumentsElements::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1529  using SloppyArgsD =
1530  CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kNewSloppyArgumentsElements>::type;
1531  using StrictArgsD =
1532  CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kNewStrictArgumentsElements>::type;
1533  using RestArgsD =
1534  CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kNewRestArgumentsElements>::type;
1535  static_assert(
1536  SloppyArgsD::GetRegisterParameter(SloppyArgsD::kArgumentCount) ==
1537  StrictArgsD::GetRegisterParameter(StrictArgsD::kArgumentCount));
1538  static_assert(
1539  SloppyArgsD::GetRegisterParameter(SloppyArgsD::kArgumentCount) ==
1540  StrictArgsD::GetRegisterParameter(RestArgsD::kArgumentCount));
1541  UseFixed(arguments_count_input(),
1542  SloppyArgsD::GetRegisterParameter(SloppyArgsD::kArgumentCount));
1543  DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
1544 }
1545 
1546 void ArgumentsElements::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1547  const ProcessingState& state) {
1548  Register arguments_count = ToRegister(arguments_count_input());
1549  switch (type()) {
1550  case CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments:
1551  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kNewSloppyArgumentsElements>(
1552  __ GetFramePointer(), formal_parameter_count(), arguments_count);
1553  break;
1554  case CreateArgumentsType::kUnmappedArguments:
1555  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kNewStrictArgumentsElements>(
1556  __ GetFramePointer(), formal_parameter_count(), arguments_count);
1557  break;
1558  case CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter:
1559  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kNewRestArgumentsElements>(
1560  __ GetFramePointer(), formal_parameter_count(), arguments_count);
1561  break;
1562  }
1563 }
1564 
1565 void AllocateElementsArray::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
1566  UseAndClobberRegister(length_input());
1567  DefineAsRegister(this);
1568  set_temporaries_needed(1);
1569 }
1570 void AllocateElementsArray::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1571  const ProcessingState& state) {
1572  Register length = ToRegister(length_input());
1573  Register elements = ToRegister(result());
1574  Label allocate_elements, done;
1575  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
1576  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1577  // Be sure to save the length in the register snapshot.
1578  RegisterSnapshot snapshot = register_snapshot();
1579  snapshot.live_registers.set(length);
1580 
1581  // Return empty fixed array if length equal zero.
1582  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(length, 0, kNotEqual, &allocate_elements,
1583  Label::Distance::kNear);
1584  __ LoadRoot(elements, RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray);
1585  __ Jump(&done);
1586 
1587  // Allocate a fixed array object.
1588  __ bind(&allocate_elements);
1589  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(
1590  length, JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray, kGreaterThanEqual,
1591  __ GetDeoptLabel(this,
1592  DeoptimizeReason::kGreaterThanMaxFastElementArray));
1593  {
1594  Register size_in_bytes = scratch;
1595  __ Move(size_in_bytes, length);
1596  __ ShiftLeft(size_in_bytes, kTaggedSizeLog2);
1597  __ AddInt32(size_in_bytes, OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray));
1598  __ Allocate(snapshot, elements, size_in_bytes, allocation_type_);
1599  __ SetMapAsRoot(elements, RootIndex::kFixedArrayMap);
1600  }
1601  {
1602  Register smi_length = scratch;
1603  __ UncheckedSmiTagInt32(smi_length, length);
1604  __ StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(elements, offsetof(FixedArray, length_),
1605  smi_length);
1606  }
1607 
1608  // Initialize the array with holes.
1609  {
1610  Label loop;
1611  Register the_hole = scratch;
1612  __ LoadTaggedRoot(the_hole, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
1613  __ bind(&loop);
1614  __ DecrementInt32(length);
1615  // TODO(victorgomes): This can be done more efficiently by have the root
1616  // (the_hole) as an immediate in the store.
1617  __ StoreFixedArrayElementNoWriteBarrier(elements, length, the_hole);
1618  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(length, 0, kGreaterThan, &loop,
1619  Label::Distance::kNear);
1620  }
1621  __ bind(&done);
1622 }

1626 constexpr Builtin BuiltinFor(Operation operation) {
1627  switch (operation) {
1628 #define CASE(name) \
1629  case Operation::k##name: \
1630  return Builtin::k##name##_WithFeedback;
1631  OPERATION_LIST(CASE)
1632 #undef CASE
1633  }
1634 }
1635 
1636 } // namespace

1640  using D = UnaryOp_WithFeedbackDescriptor;
1641  UseFixed(operand_input(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kValue));
1642  DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
1643 }
1644 
1645 template <class Derived, Operation kOperation>
1646 void UnaryWithFeedbackNode<Derived, kOperation>::GenerateCode(
1647  MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
1648  __ CallBuiltin<BuiltinFor(kOperation)>(
1649  masm->native_context().object(), // context
1650  operand_input(), // value
1651  feedback().index(), // feedback slot
1652  feedback().vector // feedback vector
1653  );
1654  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
1655 }

1662  UseFixed(right_input(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kRight));
1663  DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
1664 }

1668  MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
1669  __ CallBuiltin<BuiltinFor(kOperation)>(
1670  masm->native_context().object(), // context
1671  left_input(), // left
1672  right_input(), // right
1673  feedback().index(), // feedback slot
1674  feedback().vector // feedback vector
1675  );
1676  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
1677 }

1694 struct GetRegister;
1695 template <>
1696 struct GetRegister<Register> {
1697  static Register Get(compiler::AllocatedOperand target) {
1698  return target.GetRegister();
1699  }
1700 };
1701 template <>

1704  return target.GetDoubleRegister();
1705  }
1706 };

1709 void ConstantGapMove::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1710  const ProcessingState& state) {
1711  switch (node_->opcode()) {
1712 #define CASE(Name) \
1713  case Opcode::k##Name: \
1714  return node_->Cast<Name>()->DoLoadToRegister( \
1715  masm, GetRegister<Name::OutputRegister>::Get(target()));
1716  CONSTANT_VALUE_NODE_LIST(CASE)
1717 #undef CASE
1718  default:
1719  UNREACHABLE();
1720  }
1721 }
1722 
1723 void GapMove::SetValueLocationConstraints() { UNREACHABLE(); }
1724 void GapMove::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1725  const ProcessingState& state) {
1726  DCHECK_EQ(source().representation(), target().representation());
1727  MachineRepresentation repr = source().representation();
1728  if (source().IsRegister()) {
1729  Register source_reg = ToRegister(source());
1730  if (target().IsAnyRegister()) {
1731  DCHECK(target().IsRegister());
1732  __ MoveRepr(repr, ToRegister(target()), source_reg);
1733  } else {
1734  __ MoveRepr(repr, masm->ToMemOperand(target()), source_reg);
1735  }
1736  } else if (source().IsDoubleRegister()) {
1737  DoubleRegister source_reg = ToDoubleRegister(source());
1738  if (target().IsAnyRegister()) {
1739  DCHECK(target().IsDoubleRegister());
1740  __ Move(ToDoubleRegister(target()), source_reg);
1741  } else {
1742  __ StoreFloat64(masm->ToMemOperand(target()), source_reg);
1743  }
1744  } else {
1745  DCHECK(source().IsAnyStackSlot());
1746  MemOperand source_op = masm->ToMemOperand(source());
1747  if (target().IsRegister()) {
1748  __ MoveRepr(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer, ToRegister(target()),
1749  source_op);
1750  } else if (target().IsDoubleRegister()) {
1751  __ LoadFloat64(ToDoubleRegister(target()), source_op);
1752  } else {
1753  DCHECK(target().IsAnyStackSlot());
1754  DCHECK_EQ(ElementSizeInBytes(repr), kSystemPointerSize);
1755  __ MoveRepr(repr, masm->ToMemOperand(target()), source_op);
1756  }
1757  }
1758 }

1764 void AssertInt32::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
1765  const ProcessingState& state) {
1766  __ CompareInt32AndAssert(ToRegister(left_input()), ToRegister(right_input()),
1767  ToCondition(condition_), reason_);
1768 }

1776  DeoptimizeReason::kNotASmi, this);

1831 void CheckedInt32ToUint32::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,

1987 namespace {
1988 
1989 void JumpToFailIfNotHeapNumberOrOddball(
1990  MaglevAssembler* masm, Register value,
1991  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type, Label* fail) {
1992  if (!fail && !v8_flags.debug_code) return;
1993 
1994  static_assert(InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE + 1 ==
1995  InstanceType::ODDBALL_TYPE);
1996  switch (conversion_type) {
1997  case TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrBoolean: {
1998  // Check if HeapNumber or Boolean, jump to fail otherwise.
1999  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2000  Register map = temps.AcquireScratch();
2001 
2002 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2003  static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap + Map::kSize ==
2004  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kHeapNumberMap);
2005  __ LoadMapForCompare(map, value);
2006  if (fail) {
2007  __ JumpIfObjectNotInRange(map, StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap,
2008  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kHeapNumberMap, fail);
2009  } else {
2010  __ AssertObjectInRange(map, StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap,
2011  StaticReadOnlyRoot::kHeapNumberMap,
2012  AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
2013  }
2014 #else
2015  Label done;
2016  __ LoadMap(map, value);
2017  __ CompareRoot(map, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
2018  __ JumpIf(kEqual, &done);
2019  __ CompareRoot(map, RootIndex::kBooleanMap);
2020  if (fail) {
2021  __ JumpIf(kNotEqual, fail);
2022  } else {
2023  __ Assert(kEqual, AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
2024  }
2025  __ bind(&done);
2026 #endif
2027  break;
2028  }
2029  case TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball:
2030  // Check if HeapNumber or Oddball, jump to fail otherwise.
2031  if (fail) {
2032  __ JumpIfObjectTypeNotInRange(value, InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE,
2033  InstanceType::ODDBALL_TYPE, fail);
2034  } else {
2035  __ AssertObjectTypeInRange(value, InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE,
2036  InstanceType::ODDBALL_TYPE,
2037  AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
2038  }
2039  break;
2040  case TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber:
2041  // Check if HeapNumber, jump to fail otherwise.
2042  if (fail) {
2043  __ JumpIfNotObjectType(value, InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE, fail);
2044  } else {
2045  __ AssertObjectType(value, InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE,
2046  AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
2047  }
2048  break;
2049  }
2050 }
2051 
2052 void TryUnboxNumberOrOddball(MaglevAssembler* masm, DoubleRegister dst,
2053  Register clobbered_src,
2054  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type,
2055  Label* fail) {
2056  Label is_not_smi, done;
2057  // Check if Smi.
2058  __ JumpIfNotSmi(clobbered_src, &is_not_smi, Label::kNear);
2059  // If Smi, convert to Float64.
2060  __ SmiToInt32(clobbered_src);
2061  __ Int32ToDouble(dst, clobbered_src);
2062  __ Jump(&done);
2063  __ bind(&is_not_smi);
2064  JumpToFailIfNotHeapNumberOrOddball(masm, clobbered_src, conversion_type,
2065  fail);
2066  __ LoadHeapNumberOrOddballValue(dst, clobbered_src);
2067  __ bind(&done);
2068 }
2069 
2070 } // namespace

2072  requires(FloatType == ValueRepresentation::kFloat64 ||
2073  FloatType == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64)
2074 void CheckedNumberOrOddballToFloat64OrHoleyFloat64<
2075  Derived, FloatType>::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
2076  UseAndClobberRegister(input());
2077  DefineAsRegister(this);
2078 }
2079 template <typename Derived, ValueRepresentation FloatType>
2080  requires(FloatType == ValueRepresentation::kFloat64 ||
2081  FloatType == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64)
2082 void CheckedNumberOrOddballToFloat64OrHoleyFloat64<
2083  Derived, FloatType>::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2084  const ProcessingState& state) {
2085  Register value = ToRegister(input());
2086  TryUnboxNumberOrOddball(masm, ToDoubleRegister(result()), value,
2087  conversion_type(),
2088  __ GetDeoptLabel(this, deoptimize_reason()));
2089 }

2095 void CheckedNumberOrOddballToHoleyFloat64::GenerateCode(
2096  MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
2097  Register src = ToRegister(input());
2098  DoubleRegister dst = ToDoubleRegister(result());
2099  Label* fail = __ GetDeoptLabel(this, deoptimize_reason());
2100 
2101  Label is_not_smi, done;
2102  // Check if Smi.
2103  __ JumpIfNotSmi(src, &is_not_smi, Label::kNear);
2104  // If Smi, convert to Float64.
2105  __ SmiToInt32(src);
2106  __ Int32ToDouble(dst, src);
2107  __ Jump(&done);
2108  __ bind(&is_not_smi);
2109  JumpToFailIfNotHeapNumberOrOddball(
2110  masm, src, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball, fail);
2111  __ LoadHeapNumberOrOddballValue(dst, src);
2112  __ JumpIfNotObjectType(src, InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE, &done,
2113  Label::kNear);
2114  __ Float64SilenceNan(dst);
2115  __ bind(&done);
2116 }

2156 void EmitTruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32(
2157  MaglevAssembler* masm, Register value, Register result_reg,
2158  TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type, Label* not_a_number) {
2159  Label is_not_smi, done;
2160  // Check if Smi.
2161  __ JumpIfNotSmi(value, &is_not_smi, Label::kNear);
2162  // If Smi, convert to Int32.
2163  __ SmiToInt32(value);
2164  __ Jump(&done, Label::kNear);
2165  __ bind(&is_not_smi);
2166  JumpToFailIfNotHeapNumberOrOddball(masm, value, conversion_type,
2167  not_a_number);
2168  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2169  DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireScratchDouble();
2170  __ LoadHeapNumberOrOddballValue(double_value, value);
2171  __ TruncateDoubleToInt32(result_reg, double_value);
2172  __ bind(&done);
2173 }

2177 void CheckedObjectToIndex::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
2178  UseRegister(object_input());
2179  DefineAsRegister(this);
2180  set_double_temporaries_needed(1);
2181 }
2182 void CheckedObjectToIndex::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2183  const ProcessingState& state) {
2184  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
2185  Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
2186  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
2187  __ JumpIfNotSmi(
2188  object,
2189  __ MakeDeferredCode(
2190  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object, Register result_reg,
2191  ZoneLabelRef done, CheckedObjectToIndex* node) {
2192  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2193  Register map = temps.AcquireScratch();
2194  Label check_string;
2195  __ LoadMapForCompare(map, object);
2196  __ JumpIfNotRoot(
2197  map, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap, &check_string,
2198  v8_flags.deopt_every_n_times > 0 ? Label::kFar : Label::kNear);
2199  {
2200  DoubleRegister number_value = temps.AcquireDouble();
2201  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(number_value, object);
2202  __ TryChangeFloat64ToIndex(
2203  result_reg, number_value, *done,
2204  __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kNotInt32));
2205  }
2206  __ bind(&check_string);
2207  // The IC will go generic if it encounters something other than a
2208  // Number or String key.
2209  __ JumpIfStringMap(
2210  map, __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kNotInt32),
2211  Label::kFar, false);
2212  // map is clobbered after this call.
2213 
2214  {
2215  // TODO(verwaest): Load the cached number from the string hash.
2216  RegisterSnapshot snapshot = node->register_snapshot();
2217  snapshot.live_registers.clear(result_reg);
2218  DCHECK(!snapshot.live_tagged_registers.has(result_reg));
2219  {
2220  SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
2221  AllowExternalCallThatCantCauseGC scope(masm);
2222  __ PrepareCallCFunction(1);
2223  __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], object);
2224  __ CallCFunction(
2225  ExternalReference::string_to_array_index_function(), 1);
2226  // No need for safepoint since this is a fast C call.
2227  __ Move(result_reg, kReturnRegister0);
2228  }
2229  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(
2230  result_reg, 0, kLessThan,
2231  __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kNotInt32));
2232  __ Jump(*done);
2233  }
2234  },
2235  object, result_reg, done, this));
2236 
2237  // If we didn't enter the deferred block, we're a Smi.
2238  __ SmiToInt32(result_reg, object);
2239  __ bind(*done);
2240 }

2297 void CheckMaps::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
2298  UseRegister(receiver_input());
2299  set_temporaries_needed(MapCompare::TemporaryCount(maps_.size()));
2300 }
2301 
2302 void CheckMaps::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2303  const ProcessingState& state) {
2304  Register object = ToRegister(receiver_input());
2305 
2306  // We emit an unconditional deopt if we intersect the map sets and the
2307  // intersection is empty.
2308  DCHECK(!maps().is_empty());
2309 
2310  bool maps_include_heap_number = compiler::AnyMapIsHeapNumber(maps());
2311 
2312  // Experimentally figured out map limit (with slack) which allows us to use
2313  // near jumps in the code below. If --deopt-every-n-times is on, we generate
2314  // a bit more code, so disable the near jump optimization.
2315  constexpr int kMapCountForNearJumps = kTaggedSize == 4 ? 10 : 5;
2316  Label::Distance jump_distance = (maps().size() <= kMapCountForNearJumps &&
2317  v8_flags.deopt_every_n_times <= 0)
2318  ? Label::Distance::kNear
2319  : Label::Distance::kFar;
2320 
2321  Label done;
2322  if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
2323  __ AssertNotSmi(object);
2324  } else {
2325  if (maps_include_heap_number) {
2326  // Smis count as matching the HeapNumber map, so we're done.
2327  __ JumpIfSmi(object, &done, jump_distance);
2328  } else {
2329  __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(this, object, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2330  }
2331  }
2332 
2333  MapCompare map_compare(masm, object, maps_.size());
2334  size_t map_count = maps().size();
2335  for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count - 1; ++i) {
2336  Handle<Map> map = maps().at(i).object();
2337  map_compare.Generate(map, kEqual, &done, jump_distance);
2338  }
2339  Handle<Map> last_map = maps().at(map_count - 1).object();
2340  Label* fail = __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2341  map_compare.Generate(last_map, kNotEqual, fail);
2342  __ bind(&done);
2343 }
2344 
2345 int CheckMapsWithMigrationAndDeopt::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
2346  DCHECK_EQ(Runtime::FunctionForId(
2347  Runtime::kTryMigrateInstanceAndMarkMapAsMigrationTarget)
2348  ->nargs,
2349  1);
2350  return 1;
2351 }
2352 
2353 void CheckMapsWithMigrationAndDeopt::SetValueLocationConstraints() {

2355  set_temporaries_needed(MapCompare::TemporaryCount(maps_.size()));
2356 }
2357 
2358 void CheckMapsWithMigrationAndDeopt::GenerateCode(
2359  MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
2360  Register object = ToRegister(receiver_input());
2361 
2362  // We emit an unconditional deopt if we intersect the map sets and the
2363  // intersection is empty.
2364  DCHECK(!maps().is_empty());
2365 
2366  bool maps_include_heap_number = compiler::AnyMapIsHeapNumber(maps());
2367 
2368  // Experimentally figured out map limit (with slack) which allows us to use
2369  // near jumps in the code below. If --deopt-every-n-times is on, we generate
2370  // a bit more code, so disable the near jump optimization.
2371  constexpr int kMapCountForNearJumps = kTaggedSize == 4 ? 10 : 5;
2372  Label::Distance jump_distance = (maps().size() <= kMapCountForNearJumps &&
2373  v8_flags.deopt_every_n_times <= 0)
2374  ? Label::Distance::kNear
2375  : Label::Distance::kFar;
2376 
2377  Label done;
2378  if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
2379  __ AssertNotSmi(object);
2380  } else {
2381  if (maps_include_heap_number) {
2382  // Smis count as matching the HeapNumber map, so we're done.
2383  __ JumpIfSmi(object, &done, jump_distance);
2384  } else {
2385  __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(this, object, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2386  }
2387  }
2388 
2389  MapCompare map_compare(masm, object, maps_.size());
2390  size_t map_count = maps().size();
2391  for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count - 1; ++i) {
2392  Handle<Map> map = maps().at(i).object();
2393  map_compare.Generate(map, kEqual, &done, jump_distance);
2394  }
2395 
2396  Handle<Map> last_map = maps().at(map_count - 1).object();
2397  map_compare.Generate(
2398  last_map, kNotEqual,
2399  __ MakeDeferredCode(
2400  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot,
2401  MapCompare map_compare, CheckMapsWithMigrationAndDeopt* node) {
2402  Label* deopt = __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2403  // If the map is not deprecated, we fail the map check.
2404  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAllClear(
2405  FieldMemOperand(map_compare.GetMap(), Map::kBitField3Offset),
2406  Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit::kMask, deopt);
2407 
2408  // Otherwise, try migrating the object.
2409  __ TryMigrateInstanceAndMarkMapAsMigrationTarget(
2410  map_compare.GetObject(), register_snapshot);
2411  // Deopt even if the migration was successful.
2412  __ JumpToDeopt(deopt);
2413  },
2414  register_snapshot(), map_compare, this));
2415  // If the jump to deferred code was not taken, the map was equal to the
2416  // last map.
2417  __ bind(&done);
2418 }
2419 
2420 int CheckMapsWithMigration::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
2421  DCHECK_EQ(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kTryMigrateInstance)->nargs, 1);
2422  return 1;
2423 }
2424 
2425 void CheckMapsWithMigration::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
2426  UseRegister(receiver_input());
2427  set_temporaries_needed(MapCompare::TemporaryCount(maps_.size()));
2428 }
2429 
2430 void CheckMapsWithMigration::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2431  const ProcessingState& state) {
2432  // We emit an unconditional deopt if we intersect the map sets and the
2433  // intersection is empty.
2434  DCHECK(!maps().is_empty());
2435 
2436  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2437  Register object = ToRegister(receiver_input());
2438 
2439  bool maps_include_heap_number = compiler::AnyMapIsHeapNumber(maps());
2440 
2441  ZoneLabelRef map_checks(masm), done(masm);
2442 
2443  if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
2444  __ AssertNotSmi(object);
2445  } else {
2446  if (maps_include_heap_number) {
2447  // Smis count as matching the HeapNumber map, so we're done.
2448  __ JumpIfSmi(object, *done);
2449  } else {
2450  __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(this, object, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2451  }
2452  }
2453 
2454  // If we jump from here from the deferred code (below), we need to reload
2455  // the map.
2456  __ bind(*map_checks);
2457 
2458  RegisterSnapshot save_registers = register_snapshot();
2459  // Make sure that the object register is not clobbered by the
2460  // Runtime::kMigrateInstance runtime call. It's ok to clobber the register
2461  // where the object map is, since the map is reloaded after the runtime call.
2462  save_registers.live_registers.set(object);
2463  save_registers.live_tagged_registers.set(object);
2464 
2465  size_t map_count = maps().size();
2466  bool has_migration_targets = false;
2467  MapCompare map_compare(masm, object, maps_.size());
2468  Handle<Map> map_handle;
2469  for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count; ++i) {
2470  map_handle = maps().at(i).object();
2471  const bool last_map = (i == map_count - 1);
2472  if (!last_map) {
2473  map_compare.Generate(map_handle, kEqual, *done);
2474  }
2475  if (map_handle->is_migration_target()) {
2476  has_migration_targets = true;
2477  }
2478  }
2479 
2480  if (!has_migration_targets) {
2481  // Emit deopt for the last map.
2482  map_compare.Generate(map_handle, kNotEqual,
2483  __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap));
2484  } else {
2485  map_compare.Generate(
2486  map_handle, kNotEqual,
2487  __ MakeDeferredCode(
2488  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot,
2489  ZoneLabelRef map_checks, MapCompare map_compare,
2490  CheckMapsWithMigration* node) {
2491  Label* deopt =
2492  __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2493  // If the map is not deprecated, we fail the map check.
2494  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAllClear(
2495  FieldMemOperand(map_compare.GetMap(), Map::kBitField3Offset),
2496  Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit::kMask, deopt);
2497 
2498  // Otherwise, try migrating the object.
2499  __ TryMigrateInstance(map_compare.GetObject(), register_snapshot,
2500  deopt);
2501  __ Jump(*map_checks);
2502  // We'll need to reload the map since it might have changed; it's
2503  // done right after the map_checks label.
2504  },
2505  save_registers, map_checks, map_compare, this));
2506  // If the jump to deferred code was not taken, the map was equal to the
2507  // last map.
2508  } // End of the `has_migration_targets` case.
2509  __ bind(*done);
2510 }
2511 
2512 void CheckMapsWithAlreadyLoadedMap::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
2513  UseRegister(object_input());
2514  UseRegister(map_input());
2515 }
2516 
2517 void CheckMapsWithAlreadyLoadedMap::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2518  const ProcessingState& state) {
2519  Register map = ToRegister(map_input());
2520 
2521  // We emit an unconditional deopt if we intersect the map sets and the
2522  // intersection is empty.
2523  DCHECK(!maps().is_empty());
2524 
2525  // CheckMapsWithAlreadyLoadedMap can only be used in contexts where SMIs /
2526  // HeapNumbers don't make sense (e.g., if we're loading properties from them).
2527  DCHECK(!compiler::AnyMapIsHeapNumber(maps()));
2528 
2529  // Experimentally figured out map limit (with slack) which allows us to use
2530  // near jumps in the code below. If --deopt-every-n-times is on, we generate
2531  // a bit more code, so disable the near jump optimization.
2532  constexpr int kMapCountForNearJumps = kTaggedSize == 4 ? 10 : 5;
2533  Label::Distance jump_distance = (maps().size() <= kMapCountForNearJumps &&
2534  v8_flags.deopt_every_n_times <= 0)
2535  ? Label::Distance::kNear
2536  : Label::Distance::kFar;
2537 
2538  Label done;
2539  size_t map_count = maps().size();
2540  for (size_t i = 0; i < map_count - 1; ++i) {
2541  Handle<Map> map_at_i = maps().at(i).object();
2542  __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(map, map_at_i, kEqual, &done, jump_distance);
2543  }
2544  Handle<Map> last_map = maps().at(map_count - 1).object();
2545  Label* fail = __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2546  __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(map, last_map, kNotEqual, fail);
2547  __ bind(&done);
2548 }

2551  DCHECK_EQ(Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kTryMigrateInstance)->nargs, 1);
2552  return 1;
2553 }

2560 
2561 void MigrateMapIfNeeded::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2562  const ProcessingState& state) {
2563  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2564  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
2565  Register map = ToRegister(map_input());
2566  DCHECK_EQ(map, ToRegister(result()));
2567 
2568  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
2569 
2570  RegisterSnapshot save_registers = register_snapshot();
2571  // Make sure that the object register are not clobbered by TryMigrateInstance
2572  // (which does a runtime call). We need the object register for reloading the
2573  // map. It's okay to clobber the map register, since we will always reload (or
2574  // deopt) after the runtime call.
2575  save_registers.live_registers.set(object);
2576  save_registers.live_tagged_registers.set(object);
2577 
2578  // If the map is deprecated, jump to the deferred code which will migrate it.
2579  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAnySet(
2580  FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kBitField3Offset),
2581  Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit::kMask,
2582  __ MakeDeferredCode(
2583  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot,
2584  ZoneLabelRef done, Register object, Register map,
2585  MigrateMapIfNeeded* node) {
2586  Label* deopt = __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
2587  __ TryMigrateInstance(object, register_snapshot, deopt);
2588  // Reload the map since TryMigrateInstance might have changed it.
2589  __ LoadTaggedField(map, object, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
2590  __ Jump(*done);
2591  },
2592  save_registers, done, object, map, this));
2593 
2594  // No migration needed. Return the original map. We already have it in the
2595  // first input register which is the same as the return register.
2596 
2597  __ bind(*done);
2598 }

2700 void Int32Compare::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2701  const ProcessingState& state) {
2702  Register result = ToRegister(this->result());
2703  Label is_true, end;
2704  if (Int32Constant* constant =
2705  right_input().node()->TryCast<Int32Constant>()) {
2706  int32_t right_value = constant->value();
2707  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(ToRegister(left_input()), right_value,
2708  ConditionFor(operation()), &is_true,
2709  Label::Distance::kNear);
2710  } else {
2711  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(
2712  ToRegister(left_input()), ToRegister(right_input()),
2713  ConditionFor(operation()), &is_true, Label::Distance::kNear);
2714  }
2715  // TODO(leszeks): Investigate loading existing materialisations of roots here,
2716  // if available.
2717  __ LoadRoot(result, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
2718  __ jmp(&end);
2719  {
2720  __ bind(&is_true);
2721  __ LoadRoot(result, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
2722  }
2723  __ bind(&end);
2724 }

2738  // if available.

2741  {
2742  __ bind(&is_true);
2743  __ LoadRoot(result,
2744  flip() ? RootIndex::kFalseValue : RootIndex::kTrueValue);
2745  }

2898 
2899 void LoadTaggedFieldForContextSlot::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2900  const ProcessingState& state) {
2901  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2902  Register script_context = ToRegister(context());
2903  Register value = ToRegister(result());
2904  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2905  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
2906 
2907  // Load value from context.
2908  __ LoadTaggedField(value, script_context, offset());
2909 
2910  // Check if an ContextCell
2911  __ JumpIfSmi(value, *done);
2912  __ CompareMapWithRoot(value, RootIndex::kContextCellMap, scratch);
2913  __ JumpToDeferredIf(
2914  kEqual,
2915  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register value, Register scratch,
2916  LoadTaggedFieldForContextSlot* node, ZoneLabelRef done) {
2917  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
2918  DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireDouble();
2919  Label allocate, is_untagged;
2920  __ LoadContextCellState(scratch, value);
2921 
2922  static_assert(ContextCell::State::kConst == 0);
2923  static_assert(ContextCell::State::kSmi == 1);
2924  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(scratch, ContextCell::kSmi, kGreaterThan,
2925  &is_untagged);
2926  __ LoadContextCellTaggedValue(value, value);
2927  __ Jump(*done);
2928 
2929  __ bind(&is_untagged);
2930  {
2931  Label check_float64;
2932  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(scratch, ContextCell::kInt32, kNotEqual,
2933  &check_float64);
2934  __ LoadContextCellInt32Value(scratch, value);
2935  __ SmiTagInt32AndJumpIfSuccess(value, scratch, *done);
2936  __ Int32ToDouble(double_value, scratch);
2937  __ Jump(&allocate, Label::kNear);
2938  __ bind(&check_float64);
2939  }
2940  __ LoadContextCellFloat64Value(double_value, value);
2941 
2942  __ bind(&allocate);
2943  __ AllocateHeapNumber(node->register_snapshot(), value, double_value);
2944  __ Jump(*done);
2945  },
2946  value, scratch, this, done);
2947 
2948  __ bind(*done);
2949 }
2950 
2951 void LoadTaggedFieldByFieldIndex::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
2952  UseRegister(object_input());
2953  UseAndClobberRegister(index_input());
2954  DefineAsRegister(this);
2955  set_temporaries_needed(1);
2956  set_double_temporaries_needed(1);
2957 }
2958 void LoadTaggedFieldByFieldIndex::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
2959  const ProcessingState& state) {
2960  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
2961  Register field_index = ToRegister(index_input());
2962  Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
2963  __ AssertNotSmi(object);
2964  __ AssertSmi(field_index);
2965 
2966  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
2967 
2968  // For in-object properties, the field_index is encoded as:
2969  //
2970  // field_index = array_index | is_double_bit | smi_tag
2971  // = array_index << (1+kSmiTagBits)
2972  // + is_double_bit << kSmiTagBits
2973  //
2974  // The value we want is at the field offset:
2975  //
2976  // (array_index << kTaggedSizeLog2) + JSObject::kHeaderSize
2977  //
2978  // We could get field_index from array_index by shifting away the double bit
2979  // and smi tag, followed by shifting back up again, but this means shifting
2980  // twice:
2981  //
2982  // ((field_index >> kSmiTagBits >> 1) << kTaggedSizeLog2
2983  // + JSObject::kHeaderSize
2984  //
2985  // Instead, we can do some rearranging to get the offset with either a single
2986  // small shift, or no shift at all:
2987  //
2988  // (array_index << kTaggedSizeLog2) + JSObject::kHeaderSize
2989  //
2990  // [Split shift to match array_index component of field_index]
2991  // = (
2992  // (array_index << 1+kSmiTagBits)) << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
2993  // ) + JSObject::kHeaderSize
2994  //
2995  // [Substitute in field_index]
2996  // = (
2997  // (field_index - is_double_bit << kSmiTagBits)
2998  // << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
2999  // ) + JSObject::kHeaderSize
3000  //
3001  // [Fold together the constants]
3002  // = (field_index << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
3003  // + (JSObject::kHeaderSize - (is_double_bit << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1)))
3004  //
3005  // Note that this results in:
3006  //
3007  // * No shift when kSmiTagBits == kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1, which is the case
3008  // when pointer compression is on.
3009  // * A shift of 1 when kSmiTagBits == 1 and kTaggedSizeLog2 == 3, which
3010  // is the case when pointer compression is off but Smis are 31 bit.
3011  // * A shift of 2 when kSmiTagBits == 0 and kTaggedSizeLog2 == 3, which
3012  // is the case when pointer compression is off, Smis are 32 bit, and
3013  // the Smi was untagged to int32 already.
3014  //
3015  // These shifts are small enough to encode in the load operand.
3016  //
3017  // For out-of-object properties, the encoding is:
3018  //
3019  // field_index = (-1 - array_index) | is_double_bit | smi_tag
3020  // = (-1 - array_index) << (1+kSmiTagBits)
3021  // + is_double_bit << kSmiTagBits
3022  // = -array_index << (1+kSmiTagBits)
3023  // - 1 << (1+kSmiTagBits) + is_double_bit << kSmiTagBits
3024  // = -array_index << (1+kSmiTagBits)
3025  // - 2 << kSmiTagBits + is_double_bit << kSmiTagBits
3026  // = -array_index << (1+kSmiTagBits)
3027  // (is_double_bit - 2) << kSmiTagBits
3028  //
3029  // The value we want is in the property array at offset:
3030  //
3031  // (array_index << kTaggedSizeLog2) + OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray)
3032  //
3033  // [Split shift to match array_index component of field_index]
3034  // = (array_index << (1+kSmiTagBits)) << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
3035  // + OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray)
3036  //
3037  // [Substitute in field_index]
3038  // = (-field_index - (is_double_bit - 2) << kSmiTagBits)
3039  // << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
3040  // + OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray)
3041  //
3042  // [Fold together the constants]
3043  // = -field_index << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1-kSmiTagBits)
3044  // + OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray)
3045  // - (is_double_bit - 2) << (kTaggedSizeLog2-1))
3046  //
3047  // This allows us to simply negate the field_index register and do a load with
3048  // otherwise constant offset and the same scale factor as for in-object
3049  // properties.
3050 
3051  static constexpr int kSmiTagBitsInValue = SmiValuesAre32Bits() ? 0 : 1;
3052  static_assert(kSmiTagBitsInValue == 32 - kSmiValueSize);
3053  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
3054  __ SmiUntag(field_index);
3055  }
3056 
3057  static constexpr int scale = 1 << (kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1 - kSmiTagBitsInValue);
3058 
3059  // Check if field is a mutable double field.
3060  static constexpr int32_t kIsDoubleBitMask = 1 << kSmiTagBitsInValue;
3061  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAnySet(
3062  field_index, kIsDoubleBitMask,
3063  __ MakeDeferredCode(
3064  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object, Register field_index,
3065  Register result_reg, RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot,
3066  ZoneLabelRef done) {
3067  // The field is a Double field, a.k.a. a mutable HeapNumber.
3068  static constexpr int kIsDoubleBit = 1;
3069 
3070  // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object. The is_double bit
3071  // value doesn't matter, since negative values will stay negative.
3072  Label if_outofobject, loaded_field;
3073  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(field_index, 0, kLessThan,
3074  &if_outofobject);
3075 
3076  // The field is located in the {object} itself.
3077  {
3078  // See giant comment above.
3079  if (SmiValuesAre31Bits() && kTaggedSize != kSystemPointerSize) {
3080  // We haven't untagged, so we need to sign extend.
3081  __ SignExtend32To64Bits(field_index, field_index);
3082  }
3083  __ LoadTaggedFieldByIndex(
3084  result_reg, object, field_index, scale,
3085  JSObject::kHeaderSize -
3086  (kIsDoubleBit << (kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)));
3087  __ Jump(&loaded_field);
3088  }
3089 
3090  __ bind(&if_outofobject);
3091  {
3092  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3093  Register property_array = temps.Acquire();
3094  // Load the property array.
3095  __ LoadTaggedField(
3096  property_array,
3097  FieldMemOperand(object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset));
3098 
3099  // See giant comment above. No need to sign extend, negate will
3100  // handle it.
3101  __ NegateInt32(field_index);
3102  __ LoadTaggedFieldByIndex(
3103  result_reg, property_array, field_index, scale,
3104  OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) -
3105  ((2 - kIsDoubleBit) << (kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)));
3106  __ Jump(&loaded_field);
3107  }
3108 
3109  __ bind(&loaded_field);
3110  // We may have transitioned in-place away from double, so check that
3111  // this is a HeapNumber -- otherwise the load is fine and we don't
3112  // need to copy anything anyway.
3113  __ JumpIfSmi(result_reg, *done);
3114  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3115  Register map = temps.Acquire();
3116  // Hack: The temporary allocated for `map` might alias the result
3117  // register. If it does, use the field_index register as a temporary
3118  // instead (since it's clobbered anyway).
3119  // TODO(leszeks): Extend the result register's lifetime to overlap
3120  // the temporaries, so that this alias isn't possible.
3121  if (map == result_reg) {
3122  DCHECK_NE(map, field_index);
3123  map = field_index;
3124  }
3125  __ LoadMapForCompare(map, result_reg);
3126  __ JumpIfNotRoot(map, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap, *done);
3127  DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireDouble();
3128  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(double_value, result_reg);
3129  __ AllocateHeapNumber(register_snapshot, result_reg, double_value);
3130  __ Jump(*done);
3131  },
3132  object, field_index, result_reg, register_snapshot(), done));
3133 
3134  // The field is a proper Tagged field on {object}. The {field_index} is
3135  // shifted to the left by one in the code below.
3136  {
3137  static constexpr int kIsDoubleBit = 0;
3138 
3139  // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object. The is_double bit value
3140  // doesn't matter, since negative values will stay negative.
3141  Label if_outofobject;
3142  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(field_index, 0, kLessThan, &if_outofobject);
3143 
3144  // The field is located in the {object} itself.
3145  {
3146  // See giant comment above.
3147  if (SmiValuesAre31Bits() && kTaggedSize != kSystemPointerSize) {
3148  // We haven't untagged, so we need to sign extend.
3149  __ SignExtend32To64Bits(field_index, field_index);
3150  }
3151  __ LoadTaggedFieldByIndex(
3152  result_reg, object, field_index, scale,
3153  JSObject::kHeaderSize - (kIsDoubleBit << (kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)));
3154  __ Jump(*done);
3155  }
3156 
3157  __ bind(&if_outofobject);
3158  {
3159  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3160  Register property_array = temps.Acquire();
3161  // Load the property array.
3162  __ LoadTaggedField(
3163  property_array,
3164  FieldMemOperand(object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset));
3165 
3166  // See giant comment above. No need to sign extend, negate will handle it.
3167  __ NegateInt32(field_index);
3168  __ LoadTaggedFieldByIndex(
3169  result_reg, property_array, field_index, scale,
3170  OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) -
3171  ((2 - kIsDoubleBit) << (kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)));
3172  // Fallthrough to `done`.
3173  }
3174  }
3175 
3176  __ bind(*done);
3177 }

3266 void StoreMap::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3267  const ProcessingState& state) {
3268  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3269  // TODO(leszeks): Consider making this an arbitrary register and push/popping
3270  // in the deferred path.
3271  Register object = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
3272  DCHECK_EQ(object, ToRegister(object_input()));
3273  Register value = temps.Acquire();
3274  __ MoveTagged(value, map_.object());
3275 
3276  switch (kind()) {
3277  case Kind::kInlinedAllocation: {
3278  DCHECK(object_input().node()->Cast<InlinedAllocation>());
3279  auto inlined = object_input().node()->Cast<InlinedAllocation>();
3280  if (inlined->allocation_block()->allocation_type() ==
3281  AllocationType::kYoung) {
3282  __ StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset,
3283  value);
3284  __ AssertElidedWriteBarrier(object, value, register_snapshot());
3285  break;
3286  }
3287  [[fallthrough]];
3288  }
3289  case Kind::kInitializing:
3290  case Kind::kTransitioning:
3291  __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset, value,
3292  register_snapshot(),
3293  MaglevAssembler::kValueIsCompressed,
3294  MaglevAssembler::kValueCannotBeSmi);
3295  break;
3296  }
3297 }

3356 void LoadSignedIntDataViewElement::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3357  const ProcessingState& state) {
3358  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
3359  Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
3360  Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
3361 
3362  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3363  __ AssertObjectTypeInRange(object,
3364  FIRST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3365  LAST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3366  AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
3367  }
3368 
3369  int element_size = compiler::ExternalArrayElementSize(type_);
3370 
3371  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3372  Register data_pointer = temps.Acquire();
3373 
3374  // We need to make sure we don't clobber is_little_endian_input by writing to
3375  // the result register.
3376  Register reg_with_result = result_reg;
3377  if (type_ != ExternalArrayType::kExternalInt8Array &&
3378  !is_little_endian_constant() &&
3379  result_reg == ToRegister(is_little_endian_input())) {
3380  reg_with_result = data_pointer;
3381  }
3382 
3383  // Load data pointer.
3384  __ LoadExternalPointerField(
3385  data_pointer, FieldMemOperand(object, JSDataView::kDataPointerOffset));
3386  MemOperand element_address = __ DataViewElementOperand(data_pointer, index);
3387  __ LoadSignedField(reg_with_result, element_address, element_size);
3388 
3389  // We ignore little endian argument if type is a byte size.
3390  if (type_ != ExternalArrayType::kExternalInt8Array) {
3391  if (is_little_endian_constant()) {
3392  if (FromConstantToBool(masm, is_little_endian_input().node()) ==
3393  V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL) {
3394  DCHECK_EQ(reg_with_result, result_reg);
3395  __ ReverseByteOrder(result_reg, element_size);
3396  }
3397  } else {
3398  ZoneLabelRef keep_byte_order(masm), reverse_byte_order(masm);
3399  DCHECK_NE(reg_with_result, ToRegister(is_little_endian_input()));
3400  __ ToBoolean(
3401  ToRegister(is_little_endian_input()), CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
3402  V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? reverse_byte_order : keep_byte_order,
3403  V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? keep_byte_order : reverse_byte_order,
3404  false);
3405  __ bind(*reverse_byte_order);
3406  __ ReverseByteOrder(reg_with_result, element_size);
3407  __ bind(*keep_byte_order);
3408  if (reg_with_result != result_reg) {
3409  __ Move(result_reg, reg_with_result);
3410  }
3411  }
3412  }
3413 }

3485 void LoadDoubleDataViewElement::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3486  const ProcessingState& state) {
3487  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3488  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
3489  Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
3490  DoubleRegister result_reg = ToDoubleRegister(result());
3491  Register data_pointer = temps.Acquire();
3492 
3493  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3494  __ AssertObjectTypeInRange(object,
3495  FIRST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3496  LAST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3497  AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
3498  }
3499 
3500  // Load data pointer.
3501  __ LoadExternalPointerField(
3502  data_pointer, FieldMemOperand(object, JSDataView::kDataPointerOffset));
3503 
3504  if (is_little_endian_constant()) {
3505  if (FromConstantToBool(masm, is_little_endian_input().node()) !=
3506  V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL) {
3507  __ LoadUnalignedFloat64(result_reg, data_pointer, index);
3508  } else {
3509  __ LoadUnalignedFloat64AndReverseByteOrder(result_reg, data_pointer,
3510  index);
3511  }
3512  } else {
3513  Label done;
3514  ZoneLabelRef keep_byte_order(masm), reverse_byte_order(masm);
3515  // TODO(leszeks): We're likely to be calling this on an existing boolean --
3516  // maybe that's a case we should fast-path here and reuse that boolean
3517  // value?
3518  __ ToBoolean(
3519  ToRegister(is_little_endian_input()), CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
3520  V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? reverse_byte_order : keep_byte_order,
3521  V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? keep_byte_order : reverse_byte_order, true);
3522  __ bind(*keep_byte_order);
3523  __ LoadUnalignedFloat64(result_reg, data_pointer, index);
3524  __ Jump(&done);
3525  // We should swap the bytes if big endian.
3526  __ bind(*reverse_byte_order);
3527  __ LoadUnalignedFloat64AndReverseByteOrder(result_reg, data_pointer, index);
3528  __ bind(&done);
3529  }
3530 }
3531 
3532 void StoreDoubleDataViewElement::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3533  UseRegister(object_input());
3534  UseRegister(index_input());
3535  UseRegister(value_input());
3536  if (is_little_endian_constant()) {
3537  UseAny(is_little_endian_input());
3538  } else {
3539  UseRegister(is_little_endian_input());
3540  }
3541  set_temporaries_needed(1);
3542 }
3543 void StoreDoubleDataViewElement::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3544  const ProcessingState& state) {
3545  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
3546  Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
3547  DoubleRegister value = ToDoubleRegister(value_input());
3548  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3549  Register data_pointer = temps.Acquire();
3550 
3551  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3552  __ AssertObjectTypeInRange(object,
3553  FIRST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3554  LAST_JS_DATA_VIEW_OR_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE,
3555  AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
3556  }
3557 
3558  // Load data pointer.
3559  __ LoadExternalPointerField(
3560  data_pointer, FieldMemOperand(object, JSDataView::kDataPointerOffset));
3561 
3562  if (is_little_endian_constant()) {
3563  if (FromConstantToBool(masm, is_little_endian_input().node()) !=
3564  V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL) {
3565  __ StoreUnalignedFloat64(data_pointer, index, value);
3566  } else {
3567  __ ReverseByteOrderAndStoreUnalignedFloat64(data_pointer, index, value);
3568  }
3569  } else {
3570  Label done;
3571  ZoneLabelRef keep_byte_order(masm), reverse_byte_order(masm);
3572  // TODO(leszeks): We're likely to be calling this on an existing boolean --
3573  // maybe that's a case we should fast-path here and reuse that boolean
3574  // value?
3575  __ ToBoolean(
3576  ToRegister(is_little_endian_input()), CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
3577  V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? reverse_byte_order : keep_byte_order,
3578  V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN_BOOL ? keep_byte_order : reverse_byte_order, true);
3579  __ bind(*keep_byte_order);
3580  __ StoreUnalignedFloat64(data_pointer, index, value);
3581  __ Jump(&done);
3582  // We should swap the bytes if big endian.
3583  __ bind(*reverse_byte_order);
3584  __ ReverseByteOrderAndStoreUnalignedFloat64(data_pointer, index, value);
3585  __ bind(&done);
3586  }
3587 }

3601 }

3618  const ProcessingState& state) {

3621  context(), // context
3622  name().object(), // name
3623  TaggedIndex::FromIntptr(feedback().index()), // feedback slot
3624  feedback().vector // feedback vector
3625  );

3628  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kLoadGlobalICInsideTypeof>(
3629  context(), // context
3630  name().object(), // name
3631  TaggedIndex::FromIntptr(feedback().index()), // feedback slot
3632  feedback().vector // feedback vector
3633  );
3634  }
3635 
3636  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
