3679 void CheckValueEqualsString::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3680  using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kStringEqual>::type;
3681  UseFixed(target_input(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLeft));
3682  RequireSpecificTemporary(D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength));
3683 }
3684 void CheckValueEqualsString::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3685  const ProcessingState& state) {
3686  using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kStringEqual>::type;
3687 
3688  ZoneLabelRef end(masm);
3689  DCHECK_EQ(D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLeft), ToRegister(target_input()));
3690  Register target = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLeft);
3691  // Maybe the string is internalized already, do a fast reference check first.
3692  __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(target, value().object(), kEqual, *end,
3693  Label::kNear);
3694 
3695  __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(this, target, deoptimize_reason());
3696  __ JumpIfString(
3697  target,
3698  __ MakeDeferredCode(
3699  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, CheckValueEqualsString* node,
3700  ZoneLabelRef end, DeoptimizeReason deoptimize_reason) {
3701  Register target = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLeft);
3702  Register string_length = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength);
3703  __ StringLength(string_length, target);
3704  Label* fail = __ GetDeoptLabel(node, deoptimize_reason);
3705  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(string_length, node->value().length(),
3706  kNotEqual, fail);
3707  RegisterSnapshot snapshot = node->register_snapshot();
3708  {
3709  SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
3710  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kStringEqual>(
3711  node->target_input(), // left
3712  node->value().object(), // right
3713  string_length // length
3714  );
3715  save_register_state.DefineSafepoint();
3716  // Compare before restoring registers, so that the deopt below has
3717  // the correct register set.
3718  __ CompareRoot(kReturnRegister0, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
3719  }
3720  __ EmitEagerDeoptIf(kNotEqual, deoptimize_reason, node);
3721  __ Jump(*end);
3722  },
3723  this, end, deoptimize_reason()));
3724 
3725  __ EmitEagerDeopt(this, deoptimize_reason());
3726 
3727  __ bind(*end);
3728 }

3795 void CheckCacheIndicesNotCleared::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3796  UseRegister(indices_input());
3797  UseRegister(length_input());
3798 }
3799 void CheckCacheIndicesNotCleared::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3800  const ProcessingState& state) {
3801  Register indices = ToRegister(indices_input());
3802  Register length = ToRegister(length_input());
3803  __ AssertNotSmi(indices);
3804 
3805  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3806  __ AssertObjectType(indices, FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE,
3807  AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAFixedArray);
3808  }
3809  Label done;
3810  // If the cache length is zero, we don't have any indices, so we know this is
3811  // ok even though the indices are the empty array.
3812  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(length, 0, kEqual, &done);
3813  // Otherwise, an empty array with non-zero required length is not valid.
3814  __ JumpIfRoot(indices, RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray,
3815  __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongEnumIndices));
3816  __ bind(&done);
3817 }

3819 void CheckTypedArrayBounds::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3820  UseRegister(index_input());
3821  if (length_input().node()->Is<IntPtrConstant>()) {
3822  UseAny(length_input());
3823  set_temporaries_needed(1);
3824  } else {
3825  UseRegister(length_input());
3826  }
3827 }
3828 void CheckTypedArrayBounds::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
3829  const ProcessingState& state) {
3830  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3831  Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
3832  Register length = Register::no_reg();
3833  if (auto length_constant = length_input().node()->TryCast<IntPtrConstant>()) {
3834  length = temps.Acquire();
3835  __ Move(length, length_constant->value());
3836  } else {
3837  length = ToRegister(length_input());
3838  }
3839  // The index must be a zero-extended Uint32 for this to work.
3840 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3841  // All Word32 values are been signed-extended in Register in RISCV.
3842  __ ZeroExtendWord(index, index);
3843 #endif
3844  __ AssertZeroExtended(index);
3845  __ CompareIntPtrAndJumpIf(
3846  index, length, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual,
3847  __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds));
3848 }

3858  NegateCondition(ToCondition(condition())), fail);

3865 void StoreContextSlotWithWriteBarrier::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
3866  UseFixed(context_input(), WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister());
3867  UseRegister(new_value_input());
3868  set_temporaries_needed(2);
3869  set_double_temporaries_needed(1);

3871 
3872 void StoreContextSlotWithWriteBarrier::GenerateCode(
3873  MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
3874  using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kDetachContextCell>::type;
3875  __ RecordComment("StoreContextSlotWithWriteBarrier");
3876  ZoneLabelRef do_normal_store(masm);
3877  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
3878  // TODO(leszeks): Consider making this an arbitrary register and push/popping
3879  // in the deferred path.
3880  Register context = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
3881  Register new_value = ToRegister(new_value_input());
3882  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
3883  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3884  Register old_value = temps.Acquire();
3885  __ LoadTaggedField(old_value, context, offset());
3886 
3887  __ JumpIfSmi(old_value, *do_normal_store);
3888  __ CompareMapWithRoot(old_value, RootIndex::kContextCellMap, scratch);
3889  __ JumpToDeferredIf(
3890  kEqual,
3891  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register context, Register old_value,
3892  Register new_value, Register scratch,
3893  StoreContextSlotWithWriteBarrier* node, ZoneLabelRef do_normal_store,
3894  ZoneLabelRef done) {
3895  __ JumpIfRoot(old_value, RootIndex::kUndefinedContextCell,
3896  *do_normal_store);
3897  {
3898  // Since we compiled without context specialization, we detach the
3899  // context cells.
3900  RegisterSnapshot snapshot = node->register_snapshot();
3901  SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
3902  if (new_value == D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kTheContext)) {
3903  // Be sure not to clobber new_value.
3904  if (context == D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kNewValue)) {
3905  __ Move(scratch, new_value);
3906  new_value = scratch;
3907  } else {
3908  __ Move(D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kNewValue), new_value);
3909  new_value = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kNewValue);
3910  }
3911  }
3912  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kDetachContextCell>(context, new_value,
3913  node->index());
3914  save_register_state.DefineSafepointWithLazyDeopt(
3915  node->lazy_deopt_info());
3916  }
3917  __ Jump(*done);
3918  },
3919  context, old_value, new_value, scratch, this, do_normal_store, done);
3920 
3921  __ bind(*do_normal_store);
3922  __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
3923  context, offset(), new_value, register_snapshot(),
3924  new_value_input().node()->decompresses_tagged_result()
3925  ? MaglevAssembler::kValueIsDecompressed
3926  : MaglevAssembler::kValueIsCompressed,
3927  MaglevAssembler::kValueCanBeSmi);
3928  __ bind(*done);
3929 }

3967 void CheckStringOrStringWrapper::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,

3970 
3971  if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
3972  __ AssertNotSmi(object);

3975  DeoptimizeReason::kNotAStringOrStringWrapper);

3994  deopt);

4083 void CheckHoleyFloat64NotHole::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,

4085  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
4086  Register scratch = temps.AcquireScratch();
4087  __ JumpIfHoleNan(ToDoubleRegister(float64_input()), scratch,
4088  __ GetDeoptLabel(this, DeoptimizeReason::kHole),
4089  Label::kFar);
4090 }

4096 void ConvertHoleToUndefined::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4097  const ProcessingState& state) {
4098  Label done;
4099  DCHECK_EQ(ToRegister(object_input()), ToRegister(result()));
4100  __ JumpIfNotRoot(ToRegister(object_input()), RootIndex::kTheHoleValue, &done);
4101  __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4102  __ bind(&done);

4105 int ConvertReceiver::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
4106  using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kToObject>::type;
4107  return D::GetStackParameterCount();
4108 }
4109 void ConvertReceiver::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4110  using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kToObject>::type;
4111  static_assert(D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kInput) == kReturnRegister0);
4112  UseFixed(receiver_input(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kInput));
4113  DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
4114 }
4115 void ConvertReceiver::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4116  const ProcessingState& state) {
4117  Label convert_to_object, done;
4118  Register receiver = ToRegister(receiver_input());
4119  __ JumpIfSmi(
4120  receiver, &convert_to_object,
4121  v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::Distance::kFar : Label::Distance::kNear);
4122 
4123  // If {receiver} is not primitive, no need to move it to {result}, since
4124  // they share the same register.
4125  DCHECK_EQ(receiver, ToRegister(result()));
4126  __ JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(receiver, &done);
4127 
4128  compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker = masm->compilation_info()->broker();
4129  if (mode_ != ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined) {
4130  Label convert_global_proxy;
4131  __ JumpIfRoot(receiver, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, &convert_global_proxy,
4132  Label::Distance::kNear);
4133  __ JumpIfNotRoot(
4134  receiver, RootIndex::kNullValue, &convert_to_object,
4135  v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::Distance::kFar : Label::Distance::kNear);
4136  __ bind(&convert_global_proxy);
4137  // Patch receiver to global proxy.
4138  __ Move(ToRegister(result()),
4139  native_context_.global_proxy_object(broker).object());
4140  __ Jump(&done);
4141  }
4142 
4143  __ bind(&convert_to_object);
4144  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kToObject>(native_context_.object(),
4145  receiver_input());
4146  __ bind(&done);
4147 }

4149 int CheckDerivedConstructResult::MaxCallStackArgs() const { return 0; }
4150 void CheckDerivedConstructResult::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4151  UseRegister(construct_result_input());
4152  DefineSameAsFirst(this);
4153 }
4154 void CheckDerivedConstructResult::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4155  const ProcessingState& state) {
4156  Register construct_result = ToRegister(construct_result_input());
4157 
4158  DCHECK_EQ(construct_result, ToRegister(result()));
4159 
4160  // If the result is an object (in the ECMA sense), we should get rid
4161  // of the receiver and use the result; see ECMA-262 section 13.2.2-7
4162  // on page 74.
4163  Label done, do_throw;
4164 
4165  __ CompareRoot(construct_result, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4166  __ Assert(kNotEqual, AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
4167 
4168  // If the result is a smi, it is *not* an object in the ECMA sense.
4169  __ JumpIfSmi(construct_result, &do_throw, Label::Distance::kNear);
4170 
4171  // Check if the type of the result is not an object in the ECMA sense.
4172  __ JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(construct_result, &done, Label::Distance::kNear);
4173 
4174  // Throw away the result of the constructor invocation and use the
4175  // implicit receiver as the result.
4176  __ bind(&do_throw);
4177  __ Jump(__ MakeDeferredCode(
4178  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, CheckDerivedConstructResult* node) {
4179  __ Move(kContextRegister, masm->native_context().object());
4180  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstructorReturnedNonObject);
4181  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(node);
4182  __ Abort(AbortReason::kUnexpectedReturnFromThrow);
4183  },
4184  this));
4185 
4186  __ bind(&done);
4187 }
4188 
4189 int CheckConstructResult::MaxCallStackArgs() const { return 0; }
4190 void CheckConstructResult::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4191  UseRegister(construct_result_input());
4192  UseRegister(implicit_receiver_input());
4193  DefineSameAsFirst(this);
4194 }
4195 void CheckConstructResult::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4196  const ProcessingState& state) {
4197  Register construct_result = ToRegister(construct_result_input());
4198  Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
4199 
4200  DCHECK_EQ(construct_result, result_reg);
4201 
4202  // If the result is an object (in the ECMA sense), we should get rid
4203  // of the receiver and use the result; see ECMA-262 section 13.2.2-7
4204  // on page 74.
4205  Label done, use_receiver;
4206 
4207  // If the result is undefined, we'll use the implicit receiver.
4208  __ JumpIfRoot(construct_result, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, &use_receiver,
4209  Label::Distance::kNear);
4210 
4211  // If the result is a smi, it is *not* an object in the ECMA sense.
4212  __ JumpIfSmi(construct_result, &use_receiver, Label::Distance::kNear);
4213 
4214  // Check if the type of the result is not an object in the ECMA sense.
4215  __ JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(construct_result, &done, Label::Distance::kNear);
4216 
4217  // Throw away the result of the constructor invocation and use the
4218  // implicit receiver as the result.
4219  __ bind(&use_receiver);
4220  Register implicit_receiver = ToRegister(implicit_receiver_input());
4221  __ Move(result_reg, implicit_receiver);
4222 
4223  __ bind(&done);
4224 }

4438 int HasInPrototypeChain::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
4439  DCHECK_EQ(2, Runtime::FunctionForId(Runtime::kHasInPrototypeChain)->nargs);
4440  return 2;
4441 }
4442 void HasInPrototypeChain::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4443  UseRegister(object());
4444  DefineAsRegister(this);
4445  set_temporaries_needed(2);
4446 }
4447 void HasInPrototypeChain::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4448  const ProcessingState& state) {
4449  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
4450  Register object_reg = ToRegister(object());
4451  Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
4452 
4453  Label return_false, return_true;
4454  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
4455 
4456  __ JumpIfSmi(object_reg, &return_false,
4457  v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::kFar : Label::kNear);
4458 
4459  // Loop through the prototype chain looking for the {prototype}.
4460  Register map = temps.Acquire();
4461  __ LoadMap(map, object_reg);
4462  Label loop;
4463  {
4464  __ bind(&loop);
4465  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4466  // Check if we can determine the prototype directly from the {object_map}.
4467  ZoneLabelRef if_objectisdirect(masm);
4468  Register instance_type = scratch;
4469  Condition jump_cond = __ CompareInstanceTypeRange(
4470  map, instance_type, FIRST_TYPE, LAST_SPECIAL_RECEIVER_TYPE);
4471  __ JumpToDeferredIf(
4472  jump_cond,
4473  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, RegisterSnapshot snapshot,
4474  Register object_reg, Register map, Register instance_type,
4475  Register result_reg, HasInPrototypeChain* node,
4476  ZoneLabelRef if_objectisdirect, ZoneLabelRef done) {
4477  Label return_runtime;
4478  // The {object_map} is a special receiver map or a primitive map,
4479  // check if we need to use the if_objectisspecial path in the runtime.
4480  __ JumpIfEqual(instance_type, JS_PROXY_TYPE, &return_runtime);
4481 
4482  int mask = Map::Bits1::HasNamedInterceptorBit::kMask |
4483  Map::Bits1::IsAccessCheckNeededBit::kMask;
4484  __ TestUint8AndJumpIfAllClear(
4485  FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kBitFieldOffset), mask,
4486  *if_objectisdirect);
4487 
4488  __ bind(&return_runtime);
4489  {
4490  snapshot.live_registers.clear(result_reg);
4491  SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
4492  __ Push(object_reg, node->prototype().object());
4493  __ Move(kContextRegister, masm->native_context().object());
4494  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kHasInPrototypeChain, 2);
4495  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerPoint(node);
4496  save_register_state.DefineSafepointWithLazyDeopt(
4497  node->lazy_deopt_info());
4498  __ Move(result_reg, kReturnRegister0);
4499  }
4500  __ Jump(*done);
4501  },
4502  register_snapshot(), object_reg, map, instance_type, result_reg, this,
4503  if_objectisdirect, done);
4504  instance_type = Register::no_reg();
4505 
4506  __ bind(*if_objectisdirect);
4507  // Check the current {object} prototype.
4508  Register object_prototype = scratch;
4509  __ LoadTaggedField(object_prototype, map, Map::kPrototypeOffset);
4510  __ JumpIfRoot(object_prototype, RootIndex::kNullValue, &return_false,
4511  v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::kFar : Label::kNear);
4512  __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(object_prototype, prototype().object(), kEqual,
4513  &return_true, Label::kNear);
4514 
4515  // Continue with the prototype.
4516  __ AssertNotSmi(object_prototype);
4517  __ LoadMap(map, object_prototype);
4518  __ Jump(&loop);
4519  }
4520 
4521  __ bind(&return_true);
4522  __ LoadRoot(result_reg, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
4523  __ Jump(*done, Label::kNear);
4524 
4525  __ bind(&return_false);
4526  __ LoadRoot(result_reg, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
4527  __ bind(*done);
4528 }

4551 void LogicalNot::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4552  const ProcessingState& state) {
4553  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4554  // LogicalNot expects either TrueValue or FalseValue.
4555  Label next;
4556  __ JumpIf(__ IsRootConstant(value(), RootIndex::kFalseValue), &next);
4557  __ JumpIf(__ IsRootConstant(value(), RootIndex::kTrueValue), &next);
4558  __ Abort(AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
4559  __ bind(&next);
4560  }
4561 
4562  Label return_false, done;
4563  __ JumpIf(__ IsRootConstant(value(), RootIndex::kTrueValue), &return_false);
4564  __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kTrueValue);
4565  __ Jump(&done);
4566 
4567  __ bind(&return_false);
4568  __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kFalseValue);
4569 
4570  __ bind(&done);
4571 }

4653 void DefineNamedOwnGeneric::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,

4656  context(), // context
4657  object_input(), // receiver
4658  name().object(), // name
4659  value_input(), // value
4660  TaggedIndex::FromIntptr(feedback().index()), // feedback slot
4661  feedback().vector // feedback vector
4662  );
4663  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
4664 }

4673 void UpdateJSArrayLength::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4674  const ProcessingState& state) {
4675  Register length = ToRegister(length_input());
4676  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
4677  Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
4678  DCHECK_EQ(length, ToRegister(result()));
4679 
4680  Label done, tag_length;
4681  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4682  __ AssertObjectType(object, JS_ARRAY_TYPE, AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
4683  static_assert(Internals::IsValidSmi(FixedArray::kMaxLength),
4684  "MaxLength not a Smi");
4685  __ CompareInt32AndAssert(index, FixedArray::kMaxLength, kUnsignedLessThan,
4686  AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
4687  }
4688  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(index, length, kUnsignedLessThan, &tag_length,
4689  Label::kNear);
4690  __ IncrementInt32(index); // This cannot overflow.
4691  __ SmiTag(length, index);
4692  __ StoreTaggedSignedField(object, JSArray::kLengthOffset, length);
4693  __ Jump(&done, Label::kNear);
4694  __ bind(&tag_length);
4695  __ SmiTag(length);
4696  __ bind(&done);
4697 }

4715 void MaybeGrowFastElements::SetValueLocationConstraints() {

4718  UseRegister(index_input());
4719  UseRegister(elements_length_input());

4721  set_temporaries_needed(1);
4722  }
4723  DefineSameAsFirst(this);
4724 }
4725 void MaybeGrowFastElements::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4726  const ProcessingState& state) {
4727  Register elements = ToRegister(elements_input());
4728  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
4729  Register index = ToRegister(index_input());
4730  Register elements_length = ToRegister(elements_length_input());
4731  DCHECK_EQ(elements, ToRegister(result()));
4732 
4733  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
4734 
4735  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(
4736  index, elements_length, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual,
4737  __ MakeDeferredCode(
4738  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, ZoneLabelRef done, Register object,
4739  Register index, Register result_reg, MaybeGrowFastElements* node) {
4740  {
4741  RegisterSnapshot snapshot = node->register_snapshot();
4742  snapshot.live_registers.clear(result_reg);
4743  snapshot.live_tagged_registers.clear(result_reg);
4744  SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
4745  using D = GrowArrayElementsDescriptor;
4746  if (index == D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kObject)) {
4747  // That implies that the first parameter move will clobber the
4748  // index value. So we use the result register as temporary.
4749  // TODO(leszeks): Use parallel moves to resolve cases like this.
4750  __ SmiTag(result_reg, index);
4751  index = result_reg;
4752  } else {
4753  __ SmiTag(index);
4754  }
4755  if (IsDoubleElementsKind(node->elements_kind())) {
4756  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kGrowFastDoubleElements>(object, index);
4757  } else {
4758  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kGrowFastSmiOrObjectElements>(object,
4759  index);
4760  }
4761  save_register_state.DefineSafepoint();
4762  __ Move(result_reg, kReturnRegister0);
4763  }
4764  __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(node, result_reg,
4765  DeoptimizeReason::kCouldNotGrowElements);
4766  __ Jump(*done);
4767  },
4768  done, object, index, elements, this));
4769 
4770  __ bind(*done);
4771 }

4773 void ExtendPropertiesBackingStore::SetValueLocationConstraints() {

4775  UseRegister(object_input());

4777  set_temporaries_needed(2);

4779 
4780 void ExtendPropertiesBackingStore::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4781  const ProcessingState& state) {
4782  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
4783  Register old_property_array = ToRegister(property_array_input());
4784  Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
4785  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
4786  Register new_property_array =
4787  result_reg == object || result_reg == old_property_array ? temps.Acquire()
4788  : result_reg;
4789  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4790  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, old_property_array, new_property_array, scratch));
4791 
4792  int new_length = old_length_ + JSObject::kFieldsAdded;
4793 
4794  // Allocate new PropertyArray.
4795  {
4796  RegisterSnapshot snapshot = register_snapshot();
4797  // old_property_array needs to be live, since we'll read data from it.
4798  // Object needs to be live, since we write the new property array into it.
4799  snapshot.live_registers.set(object);
4800  snapshot.live_registers.set(old_property_array);
4801  snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(object);
4802  snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(old_property_array);
4803 
4804  Register size_in_bytes = scratch;
4805  __ Move(size_in_bytes, PropertyArray::SizeFor(new_length));
4806  __ Allocate(snapshot, new_property_array, size_in_bytes,
4807  AllocationType::kYoung);
4808  __ SetMapAsRoot(new_property_array, RootIndex::kPropertyArrayMap);
4809  }
4810 
4811  // Copy existing properties over.
4812  {
4813  RegisterSnapshot snapshot = register_snapshot();
4814  snapshot.live_registers.set(object);
4815  snapshot.live_registers.set(old_property_array);
4816  snapshot.live_registers.set(new_property_array);
4817  snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(object);
4818  snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(old_property_array);
4819  snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(new_property_array);
4820 
4821  for (int i = 0; i < old_length_; ++i) {
4822  __ LoadTaggedFieldWithoutDecompressing(
4823  scratch, old_property_array, PropertyArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i));
4824 
4825  __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
4826  new_property_array, PropertyArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i), scratch,
4827  snapshot, MaglevAssembler::kValueIsCompressed,
4828  MaglevAssembler::kValueCanBeSmi);
4829  }
4830  }
4831 
4832  // Initialize new properties to undefined.
4833  __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4834  for (int i = 0; i < JSObject::kFieldsAdded; ++i) {
4835  __ StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(
4836  new_property_array, PropertyArray::OffsetOfElementAt(old_length_ + i),
4837  scratch);
4838  }
4839 
4840  // Read the hash.
4841  if (old_length_ == 0) {
4842  // The object might still have a hash, stored in properties_or_hash. If
4843  // properties_or_hash is a SMI, then it's the hash. It can also be an empty
4844  // PropertyArray.
4845  __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset);
4846 
4847  Label done;
4848  __ JumpIfSmi(scratch, &done);
4849 
4850  __ Move(scratch, PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel);
4851 
4852  __ bind(&done);
4853  __ SmiUntag(scratch);
4854  __ ShiftLeft(scratch, PropertyArray::HashField::kShift);
4855  } else {
4856  __ LoadTaggedField(scratch, old_property_array,
4857  PropertyArray::kLengthAndHashOffset);
4858  __ SmiUntag(scratch);
4859  __ AndInt32(scratch, PropertyArray::HashField::kMask);
4860  }
4861 
4862  // Add the new length and write the length-and-hash field.
4863  static_assert(PropertyArray::LengthField::kShift == 0);
4864  __ OrInt32(scratch, new_length);
4865 
4866  __ UncheckedSmiTagInt32(scratch, scratch);
4867  __ StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(
4868  new_property_array, PropertyArray::kLengthAndHashOffset, scratch);
4869 
4870  {
4871  RegisterSnapshot snapshot = register_snapshot();
4872  // new_property_array needs to be live since we'll return it.
4873  snapshot.live_registers.set(new_property_array);
4874  snapshot.live_tagged_registers.set(new_property_array);
4875 
4876  __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
4877  object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset, new_property_array, snapshot,
4878  MaglevAssembler::kValueIsDecompressed,
4879  MaglevAssembler::kValueCannotBeSmi);
4880  }
4881  if (result_reg != new_property_array) {
4882  __ Move(result_reg, new_property_array);
4883  }
4884 }

4963 void GeneratorRestoreRegister::SetValueLocationConstraints() {

4965  UseRegister(stale_input());

4967  set_temporaries_needed(1);

4969 void GeneratorRestoreRegister::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
4970  const ProcessingState& state) {
4971  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
4972  Register temp = temps.Acquire();
4973  Register array = ToRegister(array_input());
4974  Register stale = ToRegister(stale_input());
4975  Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
4976 
4977  // The input and the output can alias, if that happens we use a temporary
4978  // register and a move at the end.
4979  Register value = (array == result_reg ? temp : result_reg);
4980 
4981  // Loads the current value in the generator register file.
4982  __ LoadTaggedField(value, array, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(index()));
4983 
4984  // And trashs it with StaleRegisterConstant.
4985  DCHECK(stale_input().node()->Is<RootConstant>());
4986  __ StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(
4987  array, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(index()), stale);
4988 
4989  if (value != result_reg) {
4990  __ Move(result_reg, value);
4991  }
4992 }

4994 int GeneratorStore::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
4995  return WriteBarrierDescriptor::GetStackParameterCount();
4996 }
4997 void GeneratorStore::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
4998  UseAny(context_input());
4999  UseRegister(generator_input());
5000  for (int i = 0; i < num_parameters_and_registers(); i++) {
5001  UseAny(parameters_and_registers(i));
5002  }
5003  RequireSpecificTemporary(WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister());
5004  RequireSpecificTemporary(WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister());
5005 }
5006 void GeneratorStore::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5007  const ProcessingState& state) {
5008  Register generator = ToRegister(generator_input());
5009  Register array = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
5010  __ LoadTaggedField(array, generator,
5011  JSGeneratorObject::kParametersAndRegistersOffset);
5012 
5013  RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot_during_store = register_snapshot();
5014  // Include the array and generator registers in the register snapshot while
5015  // storing parameters and registers, to avoid the write barrier clobbering
5016  // them.
5017  register_snapshot_during_store.live_registers.set(array);
5018  register_snapshot_during_store.live_tagged_registers.set(array);
5019  register_snapshot_during_store.live_registers.set(generator);
5020  register_snapshot_during_store.live_tagged_registers.set(generator);
5021  for (int i = 0; i < num_parameters_and_registers(); i++) {
5022  // Use WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister() as the temporary for
5023  // the value -- it'll be clobbered by StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier since
5024  // it's not in the register snapshot, but that's ok, and a clobberable value
5025  // register lets the write barrier emit slightly better code.
5026  Input value_input = parameters_and_registers(i);
5027  Register value = __ FromAnyToRegister(
5028  value_input, WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister());
5029  // Include the value register in the live set, in case it is used by future
5030  // inputs.
5031  register_snapshot_during_store.live_registers.set(value);
5032  register_snapshot_during_store.live_tagged_registers.set(value);
5033  __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
5034  array, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i), value,
5035  register_snapshot_during_store,
5036  value_input.node()->decompresses_tagged_result()
5037  ? MaglevAssembler::kValueIsDecompressed
5038  : MaglevAssembler::kValueIsCompressed,
5039  MaglevAssembler::kValueCanBeSmi);
5040  }
5041 
5042  __ StoreTaggedSignedField(generator, JSGeneratorObject::kContinuationOffset,
5043  Smi::FromInt(suspend_id()));
5044  __ StoreTaggedSignedField(generator,
5045  JSGeneratorObject::kInputOrDebugPosOffset,
5046  Smi::FromInt(bytecode_offset()));
5047 
5048  // Use WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister() as the scratch
5049  // register, see comment above. At this point we no longer need to preserve
5050  // the array or generator registers, so use the original register snapshot.
5051  Register context = __ FromAnyToRegister(
5052  context_input(), WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister());
5053  __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
5054  generator, JSGeneratorObject::kContextOffset, context,
5055  register_snapshot(),
5056  context_input().node()->decompresses_tagged_result()
5057  ? MaglevAssembler::kValueIsDecompressed
5058  : MaglevAssembler::kValueIsCompressed,
5059  MaglevAssembler::kValueCannotBeSmi);
5060 }

5087  DefineAsRegister(this);

5089 void Int32ToNumber::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5090  const ProcessingState& state) {
5091  Register object = ToRegister(result());
5092  Register value = ToRegister(input());
5093  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
5094  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5095  // Object is not allowed to alias value, because SmiTagInt32AndJumpIfFail will
5096  // clobber `object` even if the tagging fails, and we don't want it to clobber
5097  // `value`.
5098  bool input_output_alias = (object == value);
5099  Register res = object;
5100  if (input_output_alias) {
5101  res = temps.AcquireScratch();
5102  }
5103  __ SmiTagInt32AndJumpIfFail(
5104  res, value,
5105  __ MakeDeferredCode(
5106  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object, Register value,
5107  Register scratch, ZoneLabelRef done, Int32ToNumber* node) {
5108  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5109  // AllocateHeapNumber needs a scratch register, and the res scratch
5110  // register isn't needed anymore, so return it to the pool.
5111  if (scratch.is_valid()) {
5112  temps.IncludeScratch(scratch);
5113  }
5114  DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireScratchDouble();
5115  __ Int32ToDouble(double_value, value);
5116  __ AllocateHeapNumber(node->register_snapshot(), object,
5117  double_value);
5118  __ Jump(*done);
5119  },
5120  object, value, input_output_alias ? res : Register::no_reg(), done,
5121  this));
5122  if (input_output_alias) {
5123  __ Move(object, res);
5124  }
5125  __ bind(*done);
5126 }

5142  // Unlike Int32ToNumber, object is allowed to alias value here (indeed, the
5143  // code is better if it does). The difference is that Uint32 smi tagging first
5144  // does a range check, and doesn't clobber `object` on failure.

5146  object, value,

5156  },
5157  object, value, done, this));
5158  __ bind(*done);

5199 void Float64ToTagged::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5200  const ProcessingState& state) {
5201  DoubleRegister value = ToDoubleRegister(input());
5202  Register object = ToRegister(result());
5203  Label box, done;
5204  if (canonicalize_smi()) {
5205  __ TryTruncateDoubleToInt32(object, value, &box);
5206  __ SmiTagInt32AndJumpIfFail(object, &box);
5207  __ Jump(&done, Label::kNear);
5208  __ bind(&box);
5209  }
5210  __ AllocateHeapNumber(register_snapshot(), object, value);
5211  if (canonicalize_smi()) {
5212  __ bind(&done);
5213  }
5214 }

5220 void Float64ToHeapNumberForField::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5221  const ProcessingState& state) {
5222  DoubleRegister value = ToDoubleRegister(input());
5223  Register object = ToRegister(result());
5224  __ AllocateHeapNumber(register_snapshot(), object, value);
5225 }

5227 void HoleyFloat64ToTagged::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5228  UseRegister(input());
5229  DefineAsRegister(this);
5230 }
5231 void HoleyFloat64ToTagged::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5232  const ProcessingState& state) {
5233  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
5234  DoubleRegister value = ToDoubleRegister(input());
5235  Register object = ToRegister(result());
5236  Label box;
5237  if (canonicalize_smi()) {
5238  __ TryTruncateDoubleToInt32(object, value, &box);
5239  __ SmiTagInt32AndJumpIfFail(object, &box);
5240  __ Jump(*done, Label::kNear);
5241  __ bind(&box);
5242  }
5243  // Using return as scratch register.
5244  __ JumpIfHoleNan(
5245  value, ToRegister(result()),
5246  __ MakeDeferredCode(
5247  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object, ZoneLabelRef done) {
5248  // TODO(leszeks): Evaluate whether this is worth deferring.
5249  __ LoadRoot(object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5250  __ Jump(*done);
5251  },
5252  object, done));
5253 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
5254  Label not_undefined;
5255  __ JumpIfNotUndefinedNan(value, ToRegister(result()), &not_undefined);
5256  __ LoadRoot(object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5257  __ Jump(*done, Label::kNear);
5258  __ bind(&not_undefined);
5259 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
5260  __ AllocateHeapNumber(register_snapshot(), object, value);
5261  __ bind(*done);
5262 }

5494 void ConsStringMap::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5495  UseRegister(lhs());
5496  UseRegister(rhs());
5497  DefineSameAsFirst(this);
5498 }
5499 void ConsStringMap::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5500  const ProcessingState& state) {
5501  Label two_byte, ok;
5502  Register res = ToRegister(result());
5503  Register left = ToRegister(lhs());
5504  Register right = ToRegister(rhs());
5505 
5506  // Fast case for when the lhs() (which is identical to the result) happens to
5507  // contain the result for one byte string map inputs. In this case we only
5508  // need to check the rhs() and if it is one byte too, already have the result
5509  // in the correct register.
5510  bool left_contains_one_byte_res_map =
5511  lhs().node()->Is<RootConstant>() &&
5512  lhs().node()->Cast<RootConstant>()->index() ==
5513  RootIndex::kConsOneByteStringMap;
5514 
5515 #ifdef V8_STATIC_ROOTS
5516  static_assert(InstanceTypeChecker::kOneByteStringMapBit == 0 ||
5517  InstanceTypeChecker::kTwoByteStringMapBit == 0);
5518  auto TestForTwoByte = [&](Register reg, Register second) {
5519  if constexpr (InstanceTypeChecker::kOneByteStringMapBit == 0) {
5520  // Two-byte is represented as 1: Check if either of them have the two-byte
5521  // bit set
5522  if (second != no_reg) {
5523  __ OrInt32(reg, second);
5524  }
5525  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAnySet(reg,
5526  InstanceTypeChecker::kStringMapEncodingMask,
5527  &two_byte, Label::kNear);
5528  } else {
5529  // One-byte is represented as 1: Check that both of them have the one-byte
5530  // bit set
5531  if (second != no_reg) {
5532  __ AndInt32(reg, second);
5533  }
5534  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAllClear(reg,
5535  InstanceTypeChecker::kStringMapEncodingMask,
5536  &two_byte, Label::kNear);
5537  }
5538  };
5539  if (left_contains_one_byte_res_map) {
5540  TestForTwoByte(right, no_reg);
5541  } else {
5542  TestForTwoByte(left, right);
5543  }
5544 #else
5545  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5546  Register scratch = temps.AcquireScratch();
5547  static_assert(kTwoByteStringTag == 0);
5548  if (left_contains_one_byte_res_map) {
5549  __ LoadByte(scratch, FieldMemOperand(right, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
5550  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAllClear(scratch, kStringEncodingMask, &two_byte,
5551  Label::kNear);
5552  } else {
5553  __ LoadByte(left, FieldMemOperand(left, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
5554  if (left != right) {
5555  __ LoadByte(scratch, FieldMemOperand(right, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
5556  __ AndInt32(scratch, left);
5557  }
5558  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAllClear(scratch, kStringEncodingMask, &two_byte,
5559  Label::kNear);
5560  }
5561 #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS
5562  DCHECK_EQ(left, res);
5563  if (!left_contains_one_byte_res_map) {
5564  __ LoadRoot(res, RootIndex::kConsOneByteStringMap);
5565  }
5566  __ Jump(&ok, Label::kNear);
5567 
5568  __ bind(&two_byte);
5569  __ LoadRoot(res, RootIndex::kConsTwoByteStringMap);
5570  __ bind(&ok);
5571 }

5577 void UnwrapStringWrapper::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,

5583  __ bind(&done);
5584 }

5586 void StringEqual::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
5587  using D = StringEqualDescriptor;
5588  UseFixed(lhs(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLeft));
5589  UseFixed(rhs(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kRight));
5590  set_temporaries_needed(1);
5591  RequireSpecificTemporary(D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength));
5592  DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
5593 }
5594 void StringEqual::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5595  const ProcessingState& state) {
5596  using D = StringEqualDescriptor;
5597  Label done, if_equal, if_not_equal;
5598  Register left = ToRegister(lhs());
5599  Register right = ToRegister(rhs());
5600  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5601  Register left_length = temps.Acquire();
5602  Register right_length = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength);
5603 
5604  __ CmpTagged(left, right);
5605  __ JumpIf(kEqual, &if_equal,
5606  // Debug checks in StringLength can make this jump too long for a
5607  // near jump.
5608  v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::kFar : Label::kNear);
5609 
5610  if (inputs_ == StringEqualInputs::kStringsOrOddballs) {
5611  // This code is only used for strict equality. If either left or right is
5612  // not a string, then they must be non-equal (they cannot be the same
5613  // oddball, since that was checked above).
5614  __ JumpIfNotString(left, &if_not_equal);
5615  __ JumpIfNotString(right, &if_not_equal);
5616  }
5617  __ StringLength(left_length, left);
5618  __ StringLength(right_length, right);
5619  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(left_length, right_length, kNotEqual, &if_not_equal,
5620  Label::Distance::kNear);
5621 
5622  // The inputs are already in the right registers. The |left| and |right|
5623  // inputs were required to come in in the left/right inputs of the builtin,
5624  // and the |length| input of the builtin is where we loaded the length of the
5625  // right string (which matches the length of the left string when we get
5626  // here).
5627  DCHECK_EQ(right_length, D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength));
5628  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kStringEqual>(lhs(), rhs(),
5629  D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kLength));
5630  masm->DefineLazyDeoptPoint(this->lazy_deopt_info());
5631  __ Jump(&done, Label::Distance::kNear);
5632 
5633  __ bind(&if_equal);
5634  __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kTrueValue);
5635  __ Jump(&done, Label::Distance::kNear);
5636 
5637  __ bind(&if_not_equal);
5638  __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kFalseValue);
5639 
5640  __ bind(&done);
5641 }
5642

5646  DefineAsRegister(this);

5648 void TaggedEqual::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,

5652  __ JumpIf(kEqual, &if_equal, Label::Distance::kNear);
5653  __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kFalseValue);
5654  __ Jump(&done);
5655  __ bind(&if_equal);
5656  __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kTrueValue);
5657  __ bind(&done);
5658 }

5707 void TestTypeOf::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5708  const ProcessingState& state) {
5709 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM
5710  // Arm32 needs one extra scratch register for TestTypeOf, so take a maglev
5711  // temporary and allow it to be used as a macro assembler scratch register.
5712  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5713  temps.IncludeScratch(temps.Acquire());
5714 #endif

5717  __ TestTypeOf(object, literal_, &is_true, Label::Distance::kNear, true,
5718  &is_false, Label::Distance::kNear, false);
5719  // Fallthrough into true.
5720  __ bind(&is_true);
5721  __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kTrueValue);
5722  __ Jump(&done, Label::Distance::kNear);
5723  __ bind(&is_false);

5793 void ToNumberOrNumeric::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,

5797  Register object = ToRegister(value_input());
5798  Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
5799 
5800  __ JumpIfSmi(object, &move_and_return, Label::kNear);
5801  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
5802  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5803  __ CompareMapWithRoot(object, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap, scratch);
5804  __ JumpToDeferredIf(
5805  kNotEqual,
5806  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Object::Conversion mode, Register object,
5807  Register result_reg, ToNumberOrNumeric* node, ZoneLabelRef done) {
5808  {
5809  RegisterSnapshot snapshot = node->register_snapshot();
5810  snapshot.live_registers.clear(result_reg);
5811  SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
5812  switch (mode) {
5813  case Object::Conversion::kToNumber:
5814  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kToNumber>(
5815  masm->native_context().object(), object);
5816  break;
5817  case Object::Conversion::kToNumeric:
5818  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kToNumeric>(
5819  masm->native_context().object(), object);
5820  break;
5821  }
5822  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerPoint(node);
5823  save_register_state.DefineSafepointWithLazyDeopt(
5824  node->lazy_deopt_info());
5825  __ Move(result_reg, kReturnRegister0);
5826  }
5827  __ Jump(*done);
5828  },
5829  mode(), object, result_reg, this, done);
5830  __ bind(&move_and_return);
5831  __ Move(result_reg, object);
5832 
5833  __ bind(*done);
5834 }
5835

5837  using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<Builtin::kToObject>::type;
5838  return D::GetStackParameterCount();
5839 }

5843  UseFixed(value_input(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kInput));
5844  DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
5845 }
5846 void ToObject::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
5847  const ProcessingState& state) {
5848  Register value = ToRegister(value_input());
5849  Label call_builtin, done;
5850  // Avoid the builtin call if {value} is a JSReceiver.
5851  if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
5852  __ AssertNotSmi(value);
5853  } else {
5854  __ JumpIfSmi(value, &call_builtin, Label::Distance::kNear);
5855  }
5856  __ JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(value, &done, Label::Distance::kNear);
5857  __ bind(&call_builtin);
5858  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kToObject>(context(), // context
5859  value_input() // input
5860  );
5861  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
5862  __ bind(&done);
5863 }

6003  __ Abort(AbortReason::kUnexpectedReturnFromThrow);

6005  this));

6104 void Int32ToUint8Clamped::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6105  const ProcessingState& state) {

6107  Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
6108  DCHECK_EQ(value, result_reg);
6109  Label min, done;
6110  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(value, 0, kLessThanEqual, &min);
6111  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(value, 255, kLessThanEqual, &done);
6112  __ Move(result_reg, 255);
6113  __ Jump(&done, Label::Distance::kNear);
6114  __ bind(&min);
6115  __ Move(result_reg, 0);
6116  __ bind(&done);

6152 void CheckNumber::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6153  UseRegister(receiver_input());
6154 }
6155 void CheckNumber::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6156  const ProcessingState& state) {
6157  Label done;
6158  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6159  Register scratch = temps.AcquireScratch();
6160  Register value = ToRegister(receiver_input());
6161  // If {value} is a Smi or a HeapNumber, we're done.
6162  __ JumpIfSmi(
6163  value, &done,
6164  v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::Distance::kFar : Label::Distance::kNear);
6165  if (mode() == Object::Conversion::kToNumeric) {
6166  __ LoadMapForCompare(scratch, value);
6167  __ CompareTaggedRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
6168  // Jump to done if it is a HeapNumber.
6169  __ JumpIf(
6170  kEqual, &done,
6171  v8_flags.debug_code ? Label::Distance::kFar : Label::Distance::kNear);
6172  // Check if it is a BigInt.
6173  __ CompareTaggedRootAndEmitEagerDeoptIf(
6174  scratch, RootIndex::kBigIntMap, kNotEqual,
6175  DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumber, this);
6176  } else {
6177  __ CompareMapWithRootAndEmitEagerDeoptIf(
6178  value, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap, scratch, kNotEqual,
6179  DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumber, this);
6180  }
6181  __ bind(&done);
6182 }

6184 void CheckedInternalizedString::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6185  UseRegister(object_input());
6186  DefineSameAsFirst(this);
6187 }
6188 void CheckedInternalizedString::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6189  const ProcessingState& state) {
6190  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
6191  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6192  Register instance_type = temps.AcquireScratch();
6193  if (check_type() == CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck) {
6194  __ AssertNotSmi(object);
6195  } else {
6196  __ EmitEagerDeoptIfSmi(this, object, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
6197  }
6198  __ LoadInstanceType(instance_type, object);
6199  __ RecordComment("Test IsInternalizedString");
6200  // Go to the slow path if this is a non-string, or a non-internalised string.
6201  static_assert((kStringTag | kInternalizedTag) == 0);
6202  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
6203  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAnySet(
6204  instance_type, kIsNotStringMask | kIsNotInternalizedMask,
6205  __ MakeDeferredCode(
6206  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, ZoneLabelRef done,
6207  CheckedInternalizedString* node, Register object,
6208  Register instance_type) {
6209  __ RecordComment("Deferred Test IsThinString");
6210  // Deopt if this isn't a string.
6211  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAnySet(
6212  instance_type, kIsNotStringMask,
6213  __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap));
6214  // Deopt if this isn't a thin string.
6215  static_assert(base::bits::CountPopulation(kThinStringTagBit) == 1);
6216  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAllClear(
6217  instance_type, kThinStringTagBit,
6218  __ GetDeoptLabel(node, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap));
6219  // Load internalized string from thin string.
6220  __ LoadTaggedField(object, object, offsetof(ThinString, actual_));
6221  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6222  __ RecordComment("DCHECK IsInternalizedString");
6223  Label checked;
6224  __ LoadInstanceType(instance_type, object);
6225  __ TestInt32AndJumpIfAllClear(
6226  instance_type, kIsNotStringMask | kIsNotInternalizedMask,
6227  &checked);
6228  __ Abort(AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
6229  __ bind(&checked);
6230  }
6231  __ Jump(*done);
6232  },
6233  done, this, object, instance_type));
6234  __ bind(*done);
6235 }

6237 void CheckedNumberToUint8Clamped::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6238  UseRegister(input());
6239  DefineSameAsFirst(this);
6240  set_temporaries_needed(1);
6241  set_double_temporaries_needed(1);
6242 }
6243 void CheckedNumberToUint8Clamped::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6244  const ProcessingState& state) {
6245  Register value = ToRegister(input());
6246  Register result_reg = ToRegister(result());
6247  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6248  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6249  DoubleRegister double_value = temps.AcquireDouble();
6250  Label is_not_smi, min, max, done;
6251  // Check if Smi.
6252  __ JumpIfNotSmi(value, &is_not_smi);
6253  // If Smi, convert to Int32.
6254  __ SmiToInt32(value);
6255  // Clamp.
6256  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(value, 0, kLessThanEqual, &min);
6257  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(value, 255, kGreaterThanEqual, &max);
6258  __ Jump(&done);
6259  __ bind(&is_not_smi);
6260  // Check if HeapNumber, deopt otherwise.
6261  __ CompareMapWithRootAndEmitEagerDeoptIf(value, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap,
6262  scratch, kNotEqual,
6263  DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumber, this);
6264  // If heap number, get double value.
6265  __ LoadHeapNumberValue(double_value, value);
6266  // Clamp.
6267  __ ToUint8Clamped(value, double_value, &min, &max, &done);
6268  __ bind(&min);
6269  __ Move(result_reg, 0);
6270  __ Jump(&done, Label::Distance::kNear);
6271  __ bind(&max);
6272  __ Move(result_reg, 255);
6273  __ bind(&done);
6274 }

6309 
6310 int Call::MaxCallStackArgs() const { return num_args(); }
6311 void Call::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6312  using D = CallTrampolineDescriptor;
6313  UseFixed(function(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kFunction));
6314  UseAny(arg(0));
6315  for (int i = 1; i < num_args(); i++) {
6316  UseAny(arg(i));
6317  }
6318  UseFixed(context(), kContextRegister);
6319  DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
6320 }
6321 
6322 void Call::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
6323  __ PushReverse(args());
6324 
6325  uint32_t arg_count = num_args();
6326  if (target_type_ == TargetType::kAny) {
6327  switch (receiver_mode_) {
6328  case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
6329  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsNullOrUndefined>(
6330  context(), function(), arg_count);
6331  break;
6332  case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
6333  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsNotNullOrUndefined>(
6334  context(), function(), arg_count);
6335  break;
6336  case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny:
6337  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsAny>(context(), function(),
6338  arg_count);
6339  break;
6340  }
6341  } else {
6342  DCHECK_EQ(TargetType::kJSFunction, target_type_);
6343  switch (receiver_mode_) {
6344  case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
6345  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsNullOrUndefined>(
6346  context(), function(), arg_count);
6347  break;
6348  case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
6349  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsNotNullOrUndefined>(
6350  context(), function(), arg_count);
6351  break;
6352  case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny:
6353  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsAny>(
6354  context(), function(), arg_count);
6355  break;
6356  }
6357  }
6358 
6359  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
6360 }

6406 void CallSelf::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6407  const ProcessingState& state) {
6408  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6409  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6410  int actual_parameter_count = num_args() + 1;
6411  if (actual_parameter_count < expected_parameter_count_) {
6412  int number_of_undefineds =
6413  expected_parameter_count_ - actual_parameter_count;
6414  __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
6415  __ PushReverse(receiver(), args(),
6416  RepeatValue(scratch, number_of_undefineds));
6417  } else {
6418  __ PushReverse(receiver(), args());
6419  }
6420  DCHECK_EQ(kContextRegister, ToRegister(context()));
6421  DCHECK_EQ(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, ToRegister(closure()));
6422  __ Move(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister, actual_parameter_count);
6423  __ CallSelf();
6424  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
6425 }

6442 
6443 void CallKnownJSFunction::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6444  const ProcessingState& state) {
6445  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6446  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6447  int actual_parameter_count = num_args() + 1;
6448  if (actual_parameter_count < expected_parameter_count_) {
6449  int number_of_undefineds =
6450  expected_parameter_count_ - actual_parameter_count;
6451  __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
6452  __ PushReverse(receiver(), args(),
6453  RepeatValue(scratch, number_of_undefineds));
6454  } else {
6455  __ PushReverse(receiver(), args());
6456  }
6457  // From here on, we're going to do a call, so all registers are valid temps,
6458  // except for the ones we're going to write. This is needed in case one of the
6459  // helper methods below wants to use a temp and one of these is in the temp
6460  // list (in particular, this can happen on arm64 where cp is a temp register
6461  // by default).
6462  temps.SetAvailable(MaglevAssembler::GetAllocatableRegisters() -
6463  RegList{kContextRegister, kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister,
6464  kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister,
6465  kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
6466  kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister});
6467  DCHECK_EQ(kContextRegister, ToRegister(context()));
6468  DCHECK_EQ(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, ToRegister(closure()));
6469  __ Move(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister, actual_parameter_count);
6470  if (shared_function_info().HasBuiltinId()) {
6471  Builtin builtin = shared_function_info().builtin_id();
6472 
6473  // This SBXCHECK is a defense-in-depth measure to ensure that we always
6474  // generate valid calls here (with matching signatures).
6475  SBXCHECK_EQ(expected_parameter_count_,
6476  Builtins::GetFormalParameterCount(builtin));
6477 
6478  __ CallBuiltin(builtin);
6479  } else {
6480 #if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6481  __ CallJSDispatchEntry(dispatch_handle_, expected_parameter_count_);
6482 #else
6483  __ CallJSFunction(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, expected_parameter_count_);
6484 #endif
6485  }
6486  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
6487 }

6494 void CallKnownApiFunction::SetValueLocationConstraints() {

6502

6504  set_temporaries_needed(2);
6505  }
6506 }
6507 
6508 void CallKnownApiFunction::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6509  const ProcessingState& state) {
6510  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6511  __ PushReverse(receiver(), args());
6512 
6513  // From here on, we're going to do a call, so all registers are valid temps,
6514  // except for the ones we're going to write. This is needed in case one of the
6515  // helper methods below wants to use a temp and one of these is in the temp
6516  // list (in particular, this can happen on arm64 where cp is a temp register
6517  // by default).
6518  temps.SetAvailable(
6519  kAllocatableGeneralRegisters -
6520  RegList{
6521  kContextRegister,
6522  CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ActualArgumentsCountRegister(),
6523  CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::FunctionTemplateInfoRegister(),
6524  CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ApiFunctionAddressRegister()});
6525  DCHECK_EQ(kContextRegister, ToRegister(context()));
6526 
6527  if (inline_builtin()) {
6528  GenerateCallApiCallbackOptimizedInline(masm, state);
6529  return;
6530  }
6531 
6532  __ Move(CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ActualArgumentsCountRegister(),
6533  num_args()); // not including receiver
6534 
6535  __ Move(CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::FunctionTemplateInfoRegister(),
6536  i::Cast<HeapObject>(function_template_info_.object()));
6537 
6538  compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker = masm->compilation_info()->broker();
6539  ApiFunction function(function_template_info_.callback(broker));
6540  ExternalReference reference =
6541  ExternalReference::Create(&function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL);
6542  __ Move(CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ApiFunctionAddressRegister(),
6543  reference);
6544 
6545  switch (mode()) {
6546  case kNoProfiling:
6547  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimizedNoProfiling);
6548  break;
6549  case kNoProfilingInlined:
6550  UNREACHABLE();
6551  case kGeneric:
6552  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimized);
6553  break;
6554  }
6555  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
6556 }
6557 
6558 void CallKnownApiFunction::GenerateCallApiCallbackOptimizedInline(
6559  MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
6560  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6561  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6562  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6563 
6564  using FCA = FunctionCallbackArguments;
6565  using ER = ExternalReference;
6566  using FC = ApiCallbackExitFrameConstants;
6567 
6568  static_assert(FCA::kArgsLength == 6);
6569  static_assert(FCA::kNewTargetIndex == 5);
6570  static_assert(FCA::kTargetIndex == 4);
6571  static_assert(FCA::kReturnValueIndex == 3);
6572  static_assert(FCA::kContextIndex == 2);
6573  static_assert(FCA::kIsolateIndex == 1);
6574  static_assert(FCA::kUnusedIndex == 0);
6575 
6576  // Set up FunctionCallbackInfo's implicit_args on the stack as follows:
6577  //
6578  // Target state:
6579  // sp[0 * kSystemPointerSize]: kUnused <= FCA::implicit_args_
6580  // sp[1 * kSystemPointerSize]: kIsolate
6581  // sp[2 * kSystemPointerSize]: kContext
6582  // sp[3 * kSystemPointerSize]: undefined (kReturnValue)
6583  // sp[4 * kSystemPointerSize]: kTarget
6584  // sp[5 * kSystemPointerSize]: undefined (kNewTarget)
6585  // Existing state:
6586  // sp[6 * kSystemPointerSize]: <= FCA:::values_
6587 
6588  __ StoreRootRelative(IsolateData::topmost_script_having_context_offset(),
6589  kContextRegister);
6590 
6591  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "inlined CallApiCallbackOptimized builtin");
6592  __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
6593  // kNewTarget, kTarget, kReturnValue, kContext
6594  __ Push(scratch, i::Cast<HeapObject>(function_template_info_.object()),
6595  scratch, kContextRegister);
6596  __ Move(scratch2, ER::isolate_address());
6597  // kIsolate, kUnused
6598  __ Push(scratch2, scratch);
6599 
6600  Register api_function_address =
6601  CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor::ApiFunctionAddressRegister();
6602 
6603  compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker = masm->compilation_info()->broker();
6604  ApiFunction function(function_template_info_.callback(broker));
6605  ExternalReference reference =
6606  ExternalReference::Create(&function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL);
6607  __ Move(api_function_address, reference);
6608 
6609  Label done, call_api_callback_builtin_inline;
6610  __ Call(&call_api_callback_builtin_inline);
6611  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
6612  __ jmp(&done);
6613 
6614  //
6615  // Generate a CallApiCallback builtin inline.
6616  //
6617  __ bind(&call_api_callback_builtin_inline);
6618 
6619  FrameScope frame_scope(masm, StackFrame::MANUAL);
6620  __ EmitEnterExitFrame(FC::getExtraSlotsCountFrom<ExitFrameConstants>(),
6621  StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT, api_function_address,
6622  scratch2);
6623 
6624  Register fp = __ GetFramePointer();
6625 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
6626  // This is a workaround for performance regression observed on Apple Silicon
6627  // (https://crbug.com/347741609): reading argc value after the call via
6628  // MemOperand argc_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIArgcOffset);
6629  // is noticeably slower than using sp-based access:
6630  MemOperand argc_operand = ExitFrameStackSlotOperand(FCA::kLengthOffset);
6631 #else
6632  // We don't enable this workaround for other configurations because
6633  // a) it's not possible to convert fp-based encoding to sp-based one:
6634  // V8 guarantees stack pointer to be only kSystemPointerSize-aligned,
6635  // while C function might require stack pointer to be 16-byte aligned on
6636  // certain platforms,
6637  // b) local experiments on x64 didn't show improvements.
6638  MemOperand argc_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIArgcOffset);
6639 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
6640  {
6641  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Initialize v8::FunctionCallbackInfo");
6642  // FunctionCallbackInfo::length_.
6643  __ Move(scratch, num_args()); // not including receiver
6644  __ Move(argc_operand, scratch);
6645 
6646  // FunctionCallbackInfo::implicit_args_.
6647  __ LoadAddress(scratch, MemOperand(fp, FC::kImplicitArgsArrayOffset));
6648  __ Move(MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIImplicitArgsOffset), scratch);
6649 
6650  // FunctionCallbackInfo::values_ (points at JS arguments on the stack).
6651  __ LoadAddress(scratch, MemOperand(fp, FC::kFirstArgumentOffset));
6652  __ Move(MemOperand(fp, FC::kFCIValuesOffset), scratch);
6653  }
6654 
6655  Register function_callback_info_arg = kCArgRegs[0];
6656 
6657  __ RecordComment("v8::FunctionCallback's argument.");
6658  __ LoadAddress(function_callback_info_arg,
6659  MemOperand(fp, FC::kFunctionCallbackInfoOffset));
6660 
6661  DCHECK(!AreAliased(api_function_address, function_callback_info_arg));
6662 
6663  MemOperand return_value_operand = MemOperand(fp, FC::kReturnValueOffset);
6664  const int kSlotsToDropOnReturn =
6665  FC::kFunctionCallbackInfoArgsLength + kJSArgcReceiverSlots + num_args();
6666 
6667  const bool with_profiling = false;
6668  ExternalReference no_thunk_ref;
6669  Register no_thunk_arg = no_reg;
6670 
6671  CallApiFunctionAndReturn(masm, with_profiling, api_function_address,
6672  no_thunk_ref, no_thunk_arg, kSlotsToDropOnReturn,
6673  nullptr, return_value_operand);
6674  __ RecordComment("end of inlined CallApiCallbackOptimized builtin");
6675 
6676  __ bind(&done);
6677 }
6678 
6679 int CallBuiltin::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
6680  auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
6681  if (!descriptor.AllowVarArgs()) {
6682  return descriptor.GetStackParameterCount();
6683  } else {
6684  int all_input_count = InputCountWithoutContext() + (has_feedback() ? 2 : 0);
6685  DCHECK_GE(all_input_count, descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount());
6686  return all_input_count - descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount();
6687  }
6688 }
6689 
6690 void CallBuiltin::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6691  auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
6692  bool has_context = descriptor.HasContextParameter();
6693  int i = 0;
6694  for (; i < InputsInRegisterCount(); i++) {
6695  UseFixed(input(i), descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(i));
6696  }
6697  for (; i < InputCountWithoutContext(); i++) {
6698  UseAny(input(i));
6699  }
6700  if (has_context) {
6701  UseFixed(input(i), kContextRegister);
6702  }
6703  DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
6704 }
6705 
6706 template <typename... Args>
6707 void CallBuiltin::PushArguments(MaglevAssembler* masm, Args... extra_args) {
6708  auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
6709  if (descriptor.GetStackArgumentOrder() == StackArgumentOrder::kDefault) {
6710  // In Default order we cannot have extra args (feedback).
6711  DCHECK_EQ(sizeof...(extra_args), 0);
6712  __ Push(stack_args());
6713  } else {
6714  DCHECK_EQ(descriptor.GetStackArgumentOrder(), StackArgumentOrder::kJS);
6715  __ PushReverse(extra_args..., stack_args());
6716  }
6717 }
6718 
6719 void CallBuiltin::PassFeedbackSlotInRegister(MaglevAssembler* masm) {
6720  DCHECK(has_feedback());
6721  auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
6722  int slot_index = InputCountWithoutContext();
6723  switch (slot_type()) {
6724  case kTaggedIndex:
6725  __ Move(descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(slot_index),
6726  TaggedIndex::FromIntptr(feedback().index()));
6727  break;
6728  case kSmi:
6729  __ Move(descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(slot_index),
6730  Smi::FromInt(feedback().index()));
6731  break;
6732  }
6733 }
6734 
6735 void CallBuiltin::PushFeedbackAndArguments(MaglevAssembler* masm) {
6736  DCHECK(has_feedback());
6737 
6738  auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin());
6739  int slot_index = InputCountWithoutContext();
6740  int vector_index = slot_index + 1;
6741 
6742  // There are three possibilities:
6743  // 1. Feedback slot and vector are in register.
6744  // 2. Feedback slot is in register and vector is on stack.
6745  // 3. Feedback slot and vector are on stack.
6746  if (vector_index < descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount()) {
6747  PassFeedbackSlotInRegister(masm);
6748  __ Move(descriptor.GetRegisterParameter(vector_index), feedback().vector);
6749  PushArguments(masm);
6750  } else if (vector_index == descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount()) {
6751  PassFeedbackSlotInRegister(masm);
6752  DCHECK_EQ(descriptor.GetStackArgumentOrder(), StackArgumentOrder::kJS);
6753  // Ensure that the builtin only expects the feedback vector on the stack and
6754  // potentional additional var args are passed through to another builtin.
6755  // This is required to align the stack correctly (e.g. on arm64).
6756  DCHECK_EQ(descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(), 1);
6757  PushArguments(masm);
6758  __ Push(feedback().vector);
6759  } else {
6760  int slot = feedback().index();
6761  Handle<FeedbackVector> vector = feedback().vector;
6762  switch (slot_type()) {
6763  case kTaggedIndex:
6764  PushArguments(masm, TaggedIndex::FromIntptr(slot), vector);
6765  break;
6766  case kSmi:
6767  PushArguments(masm, Smi::FromInt(slot), vector);
6768  break;
6769  }
6770  }
6771 }
6772 
6773 void CallBuiltin::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6774  const ProcessingState& state) {
6775  if (has_feedback()) {
6776  PushFeedbackAndArguments(masm);
6777  } else {
6778  PushArguments(masm);
6779  }
6780  __ CallBuiltin(builtin());
6781  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
6782 }

6802 
6803 void CallCPPBuiltin::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6804  const ProcessingState& state) {
6805  using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<kCEntry_Builtin>::type;
6806  constexpr Register kArityReg = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kArity);
6807  constexpr Register kCFunctionReg = D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kCFunction);
6808 
6809  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6810  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6811  __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
6812 
6813  // Push all arguments to the builtin (including the receiver).
6814  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kReceiverIndex == 4);
6815  __ PushReverse(args());
6816 
6817  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgs == 4);
6818  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kNewTargetIndex == 0);
6819  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kTargetIndex == 1);
6820  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kArgcIndex == 2);
6821  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kPaddingIndex == 3);
6822  // Push stack arguments for CEntry.
6823  Tagged<Smi> tagged_argc = Smi::FromInt(BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgs +
6824  num_args()); // Includes receiver.
6825  __ Push(scratch /* padding */, tagged_argc, target(), new_target());
6826 
6827  // Move values to fixed registers after all arguments are pushed. Registers
6828  // for arguments and CEntry registers might overlap.
6829  __ Move(kArityReg, BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgs + num_args());
6830  ExternalReference builtin_address =
6831  ExternalReference::Create(Builtins::CppEntryOf(builtin()));
6832  __ Move(kCFunctionReg, builtin_address);
6833 
6834  DCHECK_EQ(Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(builtin()).GetReturnCount(),
6835  1);
6836  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCEntry_Return1_ArgvOnStack_BuiltinExit);
6837 }

6917 int Construct::MaxCallStackArgs() const {

6921 void Construct::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6922  using D = Construct_WithFeedbackDescriptor;
6923  UseFixed(function(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kTarget));
6924  UseFixed(new_target(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kNewTarget));
6925  UseFixed(context(), kContextRegister);
6926  for (int i = 0; i < num_args(); i++) {
6927  UseAny(arg(i));
6928  }
6929  DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
6930 }
6931 void Construct::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6932  const ProcessingState& state) {
6933  __ CallBuiltin<Builtin::kConstruct_WithFeedback>(
6934  context(), // context
6935  function(), // target
6936  new_target(), // new target
6937  num_args(), // actual arguments count
6938  feedback().index(), // feedback slot
6939  feedback().vector, // feedback vector
6940  args() // args
6941  );
6942  masm->DefineExceptionHandlerAndLazyDeoptPoint(this);
6943 }

6945 int ConstructWithSpread::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
6946  int argc_no_spread = num_args() - 1;
6947  using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<
6948  Builtin::kConstructWithSpread_WithFeedback>::type;
6949  return argc_no_spread + D::GetStackParameterCount();
6950 }
6951 void ConstructWithSpread::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
6952  using D = CallInterfaceDescriptorFor<
6953  Builtin::kConstructWithSpread_WithFeedback>::type;
6954  UseFixed(function(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kTarget));
6955  UseFixed(new_target(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kNewTarget));
6956  UseFixed(context(), kContextRegister);
6957  for (int i = 0; i < num_args() - 1; i++) {
6958  UseAny(arg(i));
6959  }
6960  UseFixed(spread(), D::GetRegisterParameter(D::kSpread));
6961  DefineAsFixed(this, kReturnRegister0);
6962 }

6969  num_args_no_spread(), // actual arguments count
6970  spread(), // spread

6972  feedback().vector, // feedback vector
6973  args_no_spread() // args
6974  );

6976 }

6983 void SetPendingMessage::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
6984  const ProcessingState& state) {
6985  Register new_message = ToRegister(value());
6986  Register return_value = ToRegister(result());
6987  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
6988  Register scratch = temps.AcquireScratch();
6989  MemOperand pending_message_operand = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6990  ExternalReference::address_of_pending_message(masm->isolate()), scratch);
6991  if (new_message != return_value) {
6992  __ Move(return_value, pending_message_operand);
6993  __ Move(pending_message_operand, new_message);
6994  } else {
6995  __ Move(scratch, pending_message_operand);
6996  __ Move(pending_message_operand, new_message);
6997  __ Move(return_value, scratch);
6998  }
6999 }

7005 void StoreDoubleField::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7006  const ProcessingState& state) {
7007  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
7008  DoubleRegister value = ToDoubleRegister(value_input());
7009 
7010  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7011  Register heap_number = temps.AcquireScratch();
7012 
7013  __ AssertNotSmi(object);
7014  __ LoadTaggedField(heap_number, object, offset());
7015  __ AssertNotSmi(heap_number);
7016  __ StoreHeapNumberValue(value, heap_number);
7017 }

7021 template <typename NodeT>
7022 void GenerateTransitionElementsKind(
7023  MaglevAssembler* masm, NodeT* node, Register object, Register map,
7024  base::Vector<const compiler::MapRef> transition_sources,
7025  const compiler::MapRef transition_target, ZoneLabelRef done,
7026  std::optional<Register> result_opt) {
7027  DCHECK(!compiler::AnyMapIsHeapNumber(transition_sources));
7028  DCHECK(!IsHeapNumberMap(*transition_target.object()));
7029 
7030  for (const compiler::MapRef transition_source : transition_sources) {
7031  bool is_simple = IsSimpleMapChangeTransition(
7032  transition_source.elements_kind(), transition_target.elements_kind());
7033 
7034  // TODO(leszeks): If there are a lot of transition source maps, move the
7035  // source into a register and share the deferred code between maps.
7036  __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(
7037  map, transition_source.object(), kEqual,
7038  __ MakeDeferredCode(
7039  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object, Register map,
7040  RegisterSnapshot register_snapshot,
7041  compiler::MapRef transition_target, bool is_simple,
7042  ZoneLabelRef done, std::optional<Register> result_opt) {
7043  if (is_simple) {
7044  __ MoveTagged(map, transition_target.object());
7045  __ StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(
7046  object, HeapObject::kMapOffset, map, register_snapshot,
7047  MaglevAssembler::kValueIsCompressed,
7048  MaglevAssembler::kValueCannotBeSmi);
7049  } else {
7050  SaveRegisterStateForCall save_state(masm, register_snapshot);
7051  __ Push(object, transition_target.object());
7052  __ Move(kContextRegister, masm->native_context().object());
7053  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kTransitionElementsKind);
7054  save_state.DefineSafepoint();
7055  }
7056  if (result_opt) {
7057  __ MoveTagged(*result_opt, transition_target.object());
7058  }
7059  __ Jump(*done);
7060  },
7061  object, map, node->register_snapshot(), transition_target,
7062  is_simple, done, result_opt));
7063  }
7064 }
7065 
7066 } // namespace

7078 void TransitionElementsKind::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7079  const ProcessingState& state) {
7080  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
7081  Register map = ToRegister(map_input());
7082  Register result_register = ToRegister(result());
7083 
7084  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
7085 
7086  __ AssertNotSmi(object);
7087  GenerateTransitionElementsKind(masm, this, object, map,
7088  base::VectorOf(transition_sources_),
7089  transition_target_, done, result_register);
7090  // No transition happened, return the original map.
7091  __ Move(result_register, map);
7092  __ Jump(*done);
7093  __ bind(*done);
7094 }

7105 void TransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap::GenerateCode(
7106  MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
7107  Register object = ToRegister(object_input());
7108  Register map = ToRegister(map_input());
7109 
7110  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
7111 
7112  __ CompareTaggedAndJumpIf(map, transition_target_.object(), kEqual, *done);
7113 
7114  GenerateTransitionElementsKind(masm, this, object, map,
7115  base::VectorOf(transition_sources_),
7116  transition_target_, done, {});
7117  // If we didn't jump to 'done' yet, the transition failed.
7118  __ EmitEagerDeopt(this, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
7119  __ bind(*done);
7120 }

7163 template <typename ResultReg>
7164 void GenerateTypedArrayLoadFromDataPointer(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7165  Register data_pointer,
7166  Register index, ResultReg result_reg,
7167  ElementsKind kind) {
7168  int element_size = ElementsKindToByteSize(kind);
7169  MemOperand operand =
7170  __ TypedArrayElementOperand(data_pointer, index, element_size);
7171  if constexpr (std::is_same_v<ResultReg, Register>) {
7172  if (IsSignedIntTypedArrayElementsKind(kind)) {
7173  __ LoadSignedField(result_reg, operand, element_size);
7174  } else {
7175  DCHECK(IsUnsignedIntTypedArrayElementsKind(kind));
7176  __ LoadUnsignedField(result_reg, operand, element_size);
7177  }
7178  } else {
7179 #ifdef DEBUG
7180  bool result_reg_is_double = std::is_same_v<ResultReg, DoubleRegister>;
7181  DCHECK(result_reg_is_double);
7182  DCHECK(IsFloatTypedArrayElementsKind(kind));
7183 #endif
7184  switch (kind) {
7185  case FLOAT32_ELEMENTS:
7186  __ LoadFloat32(result_reg, operand);
7187  break;
7188  case FLOAT64_ELEMENTS:
7189  __ LoadFloat64(result_reg, operand);
7190  break;
7191  default:
7192  UNREACHABLE();
7193  }
7194  }
7195 }
7196 
7197 template <typename ResultReg>
7198 void GenerateTypedArrayLoad(MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object,
7199  Register index, ResultReg result_reg,
7200  ElementsKind kind) {
7201  __ AssertNotSmi(object);
7202  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
7203  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7204  __ AssertObjectType(object, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE,
7205  AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
7206  }
7207 
7208  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7209  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7210 
7211  Register data_pointer = scratch;
7212  // TODO(victorgomes): Consider hoisting array data pointer.
7213  __ BuildTypedArrayDataPointer(data_pointer, object);
7214 
7215  GenerateTypedArrayLoadFromDataPointer(masm, data_pointer, index, result_reg,
7216  kind);
7217 }
7218 
7219 template <typename ResultReg>
7220 void GenerateConstantTypedArrayLoad(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7221  compiler::JSTypedArrayRef typed_array,
7222  Register index, ResultReg result_reg,
7223  ElementsKind kind) {
7224  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7225  Register data_pointer = temps.Acquire();
7226  __ Move(data_pointer, reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(typed_array.data_ptr()));
7227 
7228  GenerateTypedArrayLoadFromDataPointer(masm, data_pointer, index, result_reg,
7229  kind);
7230 }
7231 
7232 template <typename ValueReg>
7233 void GenerateTypedArrayStoreToDataPointer(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7234  Register data_pointer, Register index,
7235  ValueReg value, ElementsKind kind) {
7236  int element_size = ElementsKindToByteSize(kind);
7237  MemOperand operand =
7238  __ TypedArrayElementOperand(data_pointer, index, element_size);
7239  if constexpr (std::is_same_v<ValueReg, Register>) {
7240  __ StoreField(operand, value, element_size);
7241  } else {
7242 #ifdef DEBUG
7243  bool value_is_double = std::is_same_v<ValueReg, DoubleRegister>;
7244  DCHECK(value_is_double);
7245  DCHECK(IsFloatTypedArrayElementsKind(kind));
7246 #endif
7247  switch (kind) {
7248  case FLOAT32_ELEMENTS:
7249  __ StoreFloat32(operand, value);
7250  break;
7251  case FLOAT64_ELEMENTS:
7252  __ StoreFloat64(operand, value);
7253  break;
7254  default:
7255  UNREACHABLE();
7256  }
7257  }
7258 }
7259 
7260 template <typename ValueReg>
7261 void GenerateTypedArrayStore(MaglevAssembler* masm, Register object,
7262  Register index, ValueReg value,
7263  ElementsKind kind) {

7267  __ AssertObjectType(object, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE,
7268  AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
7269  }
7270 
7271  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7272  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7273 
7274  Register data_pointer = scratch;
7275  __ BuildTypedArrayDataPointer(data_pointer, object);
7276 
7277  GenerateTypedArrayStoreToDataPointer(masm, data_pointer, index, value, kind);
7278 }
