7406 namespace {
7407 
7408 void AttemptOnStackReplacement(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7409  ZoneLabelRef no_code_for_osr,
7410  TryOnStackReplacement* node, Register scratch0,
7411  Register scratch1, int32_t loop_depth,
7412  FeedbackSlot feedback_slot,
7413  BytecodeOffset osr_offset) {
7414  // Two cases may cause us to attempt OSR, in the following order:
7415  //
7416  // 1) Presence of cached OSR Turbofan code.
7417  // 2) The OSR urgency exceeds the current loop depth - in that case, call
7418  // into runtime to trigger a Turbofan OSR compilation. A non-zero return
7419  // value means we should deopt into Ignition which will handle all further
7420  // necessary steps (rewriting the stack frame, jumping to OSR'd code).
7421  //
7422  // See also: InterpreterAssembler::OnStackReplacement.
7423 
7424  __ AssertFeedbackVector(scratch0, scratch1);
7425 
7426  // Case 1).
7427  Label deopt;
7428  Register maybe_target_code = scratch1;
7429  __ TryLoadOptimizedOsrCode(scratch1, CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS, scratch0,
7430  feedback_slot, &deopt, Label::kFar);
7431 
7432  // Case 2).
7433  {
7434  __ LoadByte(scratch1,
7435  FieldMemOperand(scratch0, FeedbackVector::kOsrStateOffset));
7436  __ DecodeField<FeedbackVector::OsrUrgencyBits>(scratch1);
7437  __ JumpIfByte(kUnsignedLessThanEqual, scratch1, loop_depth,
7438  *no_code_for_osr);
7439 
7440  // If tiering is already in progress wait.
7441  __ LoadByte(scratch1,
7442  FieldMemOperand(scratch0, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset));
7443  __ DecodeField<FeedbackVector::OsrTieringInProgressBit>(scratch1);
7444  __ JumpIfByte(kNotEqual, scratch1, 0, *no_code_for_osr);
7445 
7446  // The osr_urgency exceeds the current loop_depth, signaling an OSR
7447  // request. Call into runtime to compile.
7448  {
7449  RegisterSnapshot snapshot = node->register_snapshot();
7450  DCHECK(!snapshot.live_registers.has(maybe_target_code));
7451  SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(masm, snapshot);
7452  DCHECK(!node->unit()->is_inline());
7453  __ Push(Smi::FromInt(osr_offset.ToInt()));
7454  __ Move(kContextRegister, masm->native_context().object());
7455  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kCompileOptimizedOSRFromMaglev, 1);
7456  save_register_state.DefineSafepoint();
7457  __ Move(maybe_target_code, kReturnRegister0);
7458  }
7459 
7460  // A `0` return value means there is no OSR code available yet. Continue
7461  // execution in Maglev, OSR code will be picked up once it exists and is
7462  // cached on the feedback vector.
7463  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(maybe_target_code, 0, kEqual, *no_code_for_osr);
7464  }
7465 
7466  __ bind(&deopt);
7467  if (V8_LIKELY(v8_flags.turbofan)) {
7468  // None of the mutated input registers should be a register input into the
7469  // eager deopt info.
7470  DCHECK_REGLIST_EMPTY(
7471  RegList{scratch0, scratch1} &
7472  GetGeneralRegistersUsedAsInputs(node->eager_deopt_info()));
7473  __ EmitEagerDeopt(node, DeoptimizeReason::kPrepareForOnStackReplacement);
7474  } else {
7475  // Continue execution in Maglev. With TF disabled we cannot OSR and thus it
7476  // doesn't make sense to start the process. We do still perform all
7477  // remaining bookkeeping above though, to keep Maglev code behavior roughly
7478  // the same in both configurations.
7479  __ Jump(*no_code_for_osr);
7480  }
7481 }
7482 
7483 } // namespace
7484 
7485 int TryOnStackReplacement::MaxCallStackArgs() const {
7486  // For the kCompileOptimizedOSRFromMaglev call.
7487  if (unit()->is_inline()) return 2;
7488  return 1;
7489 }
7490 void TryOnStackReplacement::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
7491  UseAny(closure());
7492  set_temporaries_needed(2);
7493 }
7494 void TryOnStackReplacement::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7495  const ProcessingState& state) {
7496  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7497  Register scratch0 = temps.Acquire();
7498  Register scratch1 = temps.Acquire();
7499 
7500  const Register osr_state = scratch1;
7501  __ Move(scratch0, unit_->feedback().object());
7502  __ AssertFeedbackVector(scratch0, scratch1);
7503  __ LoadByte(osr_state,
7504  FieldMemOperand(scratch0, FeedbackVector::kOsrStateOffset));
7505 
7506  ZoneLabelRef no_code_for_osr(masm);
7507 
7508  if (v8_flags.maglev_osr) {
7509  // In case we use maglev_osr, we need to explicitly know if there is
7510  // turbofan code waiting for us (i.e., ignore the MaybeHasMaglevOsrCodeBit).
7511  __ DecodeField<
7512  base::BitFieldUnion<FeedbackVector::OsrUrgencyBits,
7513  FeedbackVector::MaybeHasTurbofanOsrCodeBit>>(
7514  osr_state);
7515  }
7516 
7517  // The quick initial OSR check. If it passes, we proceed on to more
7518  // expensive OSR logic.
7519  static_assert(FeedbackVector::MaybeHasTurbofanOsrCodeBit::encode(true) >
7520  FeedbackVector::kMaxOsrUrgency);
7521  __ CompareInt32AndJumpIf(
7522  osr_state, loop_depth_, kUnsignedGreaterThan,
7523  __ MakeDeferredCode(AttemptOnStackReplacement, no_code_for_osr, this,
7524  scratch0, scratch1, loop_depth_, feedback_slot_,
7525  osr_offset_));
7526  __ bind(*no_code_for_osr);
7527 }
7528 
7529 void JumpLoop::SetValueLocationConstraints() {}
7530 void JumpLoop::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7531  const ProcessingState& state) {
7532  __ Jump(target()->label());
7533 }

7558 void BranchIfToBooleanTrue::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7559  const ProcessingState& state) {
7560  // BasicBlocks are zone allocated and so safe to be casted to ZoneLabelRef.
7561  ZoneLabelRef true_label =
7562  ZoneLabelRef::UnsafeFromLabelPointer(if_true()->label());
7563  ZoneLabelRef false_label =
7564  ZoneLabelRef::UnsafeFromLabelPointer(if_false()->label());
7565  bool fallthrough_when_true = (if_true() == state.next_block());
7566  __ ToBoolean(ToRegister(condition_input()), check_type(), true_label,
7567  false_label, fallthrough_when_true);
7568 }

7594 void BranchIfFloat64ToBooleanTrue::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7595  const ProcessingState& state) {

7605 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
7606 void BranchIfFloat64IsUndefinedOrHole::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
7607  UseRegister(condition_input());
7608  set_temporaries_needed(1);
7609 }
7610 void BranchIfFloat64IsUndefinedOrHole::GenerateCode(
7611  MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
7612  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7613  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7614  DoubleRegister input = ToDoubleRegister(condition_input());
7615  // See MaglevAssembler::Branch.
7616  bool fallthrough_when_true = if_true() == state.next_block();
7617  bool fallthrough_when_false = if_false() == state.next_block();
7618  if (fallthrough_when_false && fallthrough_when_true) {
7619  // If both paths are a fallthrough, do nothing.
7620  DCHECK_EQ(if_true(), if_false());
7621  return;
7622  }
7623  // TODO(nicohartmann): Consider providing a combined JumpIfUndefinedOrHoleNan.
7624  // Jump over the false block if true, otherwise fall through into it.
7625  __ JumpIfUndefinedNan(input, scratch, if_true()->label(), Label::kFar);
7626  if (fallthrough_when_false) {
7627  __ JumpIfHoleNan(input, scratch, if_true()->label(), Label::kFar);
7628  } else {
7629  // Jump to the false block if true.
7630  __ JumpIfNotHoleNan(input, scratch, if_false()->label(), Label::kFar);
7631  // Jump to the true block if it's not the next block.
7632  if (!fallthrough_when_true) {
7633  __ Jump(if_true()->label(), Label::kFar);
7634  }
7635  }
7636 }
7637 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
7638 
7639 void BranchIfFloat64IsHole::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
7640  UseRegister(condition_input());
7641  set_temporaries_needed(1);
7642 }
7643 void BranchIfFloat64IsHole::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7644  const ProcessingState& state) {
7645  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7646  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7647  DoubleRegister input = ToDoubleRegister(condition_input());
7648  // See MaglevAssembler::Branch.
7649  bool fallthrough_when_true = if_true() == state.next_block();
7650  bool fallthrough_when_false = if_false() == state.next_block();
7651  if (fallthrough_when_false) {
7652  if (fallthrough_when_true) {
7653  // If both paths are a fallthrough, do nothing.
7654  DCHECK_EQ(if_true(), if_false());
7655  return;
7656  }
7657  // Jump over the false block if true, otherwise fall through into it.
7658  __ JumpIfHoleNan(input, scratch, if_true()->label(), Label::kFar);
7659  } else {
7660  // Jump to the false block if true.
7661  __ JumpIfNotHoleNan(input, scratch, if_false()->label(), Label::kFar);
7662  // Jump to the true block if it's not the next block.
7663  if (!fallthrough_when_true) {
7664  __ Jump(if_true()->label(), Label::kFar);
7665  }
7666  }
7667 }

7669 void HoleyFloat64IsHole::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
7670  UseRegister(input());
7671  DefineAsRegister(this);
7672  set_temporaries_needed(1);
7673 }
7674 void HoleyFloat64IsHole::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7675  const ProcessingState& state) {
7676  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7677  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7678  DoubleRegister value = ToDoubleRegister(input());
7679  Label done, if_not_hole;
7680  __ JumpIfNotHoleNan(value, scratch, &if_not_hole, Label::kNear);
7681  __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kTrueValue);
7682  __ Jump(&done);
7683  __ bind(&if_not_hole);
7684  __ LoadRoot(ToRegister(result()), RootIndex::kFalseValue);
7685  __ bind(&done);
7686 }

7740 void BranchIfUndefinedOrNull::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7741  const ProcessingState& state) {

7743  __ JumpIfRoot(value, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, if_true()->label());
7744  __ JumpIfRoot(value, RootIndex::kNullValue, if_true()->label());

7751 void BranchIfUndetectable::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
7752  UseRegister(condition_input());
7753  set_temporaries_needed(1);
7754 }
7755 void BranchIfUndetectable::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7756  const ProcessingState& state) {
7757  Register value = ToRegister(condition_input());
7758  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7759  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7760 
7761  auto* next_block = state.next_block();
7762  if (next_block == if_true() || next_block != if_false()) {
7763  __ JumpIfNotUndetectable(value, scratch, check_type(), if_false()->label());
7764  if (next_block != if_true()) {
7765  __ Jump(if_true()->label());
7766  }
7767  } else {
7768  __ JumpIfUndetectable(value, scratch, check_type(), if_true()->label());
7769  }
7770 }

7774  set_temporaries_needed(1);
7775  DefineAsRegister(this);
7776 }
7777 void TestUndetectable::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7778  const ProcessingState& state) {
7779  Register object = ToRegister(value());
7780  Register return_value = ToRegister(result());
7781  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7782  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7783 
7784  Label return_false, done;
7785  __ JumpIfNotUndetectable(object, scratch, check_type(), &return_false,
7786  Label::kNear);
7787 
7788  __ LoadRoot(return_value, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
7789  __ Jump(&done, Label::kNear);
7790 
7791  __ bind(&return_false);
7792  __ LoadRoot(return_value, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
7793 
7794  __ bind(&done);
7795 }

7821 void Switch::SetValueLocationConstraints() {
7822  UseAndClobberRegister(value());
7823  set_temporaries_needed(1);
7824 }
7825 void Switch::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm, const ProcessingState& state) {
7826  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7827  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7828  std::unique_ptr<Label*[]> labels = std::make_unique<Label*[]>(size());
7829  for (int i = 0; i < size(); i++) {
7830  BasicBlock* block = (targets())[i].block_ptr();
7831  block->set_start_block_of_switch_case(true);
7832  labels[i] = block->label();
7833  }
7834  Register val = ToRegister(value());
7835  // Switch requires {val} (the switch's condition) to be 64-bit, but maglev
7836  // usually manipulates/creates 32-bit integers. We thus sign-extend {val} to
7837  // 64-bit to have the correct value for negative numbers.
7838  __ SignExtend32To64Bits(val, val);
7839  __ Switch(scratch, val, value_base(), labels.get(), size());
7840  if (has_fallthrough()) {
7841  // If we jump-thread the fallthrough, it's not necessarily the next block.
7842  if (fallthrough() != state.next_block()) {
7843  __ Jump(fallthrough()->label());
7844  }
7845  } else {
7846  __ Trap();
7847  }
7848 }
7849 
7850 void HandleNoHeapWritesInterrupt::GenerateCode(MaglevAssembler* masm,
7851  const ProcessingState& state) {
7852  ZoneLabelRef done(masm);
7853  Label* deferred = __ MakeDeferredCode(
7854  [](MaglevAssembler* masm, ZoneLabelRef done, Node* node) {
7855  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "HandleNoHeapWritesInterrupt");
7856  {
7857  SaveRegisterStateForCall save_register_state(
7858  masm, node->register_snapshot());
7859  __ Move(kContextRegister, masm->native_context().object());
7860  __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kHandleNoHeapWritesInterrupts, 0);
7861  save_register_state.DefineSafepointWithLazyDeopt(
7862  node->lazy_deopt_info());
7863  }
7864  __ Jump(*done);
7865  },
7866  done, this);
7867 
7868  MaglevAssembler::TemporaryRegisterScope temps(masm);
7869  Register scratch = temps.AcquireScratch();
7870  MemOperand check = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7871  ExternalReference::address_of_no_heap_write_interrupt_request(
7872  masm->isolate()),
7873  scratch);
7874  __ CompareByteAndJumpIf(check, 0, kNotEqual, scratch, deferred, Label::kFar);
7875  __ bind(*done);
7876 }

8478 // Keeping track of the effects this instruction has on known node aspects.
8479 void NodeBase::ClearElementsProperties(KnownNodeAspects& known_node_aspects) {
8480  DCHECK(IsElementsArrayWrite(opcode()));
8481  // Clear Elements cache.
8482  auto elements_properties = known_node_aspects.loaded_properties.find(
8483  KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::Elements());
8484  if (elements_properties != known_node_aspects.loaded_properties.end()) {
8485  elements_properties->second.clear();
8486  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8487  std::cout << " * Removing non-constant cached [Elements]";
8488  }
8489  }
8490 }
8491 
8492 void NodeBase::ClearUnstableNodeAspects(KnownNodeAspects& known_node_aspects) {
8493  DCHECK(properties().can_write());
8494  DCHECK(!IsSimpleFieldStore(opcode()));
8495  DCHECK(!IsElementsArrayWrite(opcode()));
8496  known_node_aspects.ClearUnstableNodeAspects();
8497 }
8498 
8499 void StoreMap::ClearUnstableNodeAspects(KnownNodeAspects& known_node_aspects) {
8500  switch (kind()) {
8501  case Kind::kInitializing:
8502  case Kind::kInlinedAllocation:
8503  return;
8504  case Kind::kTransitioning: {
8505  if (NodeInfo* node_info =
8506  known_node_aspects.TryGetInfoFor(object_input().node())) {
8507  if (node_info->possible_maps_are_known() &&
8508  node_info->possible_maps().size() == 1) {
8509  compiler::MapRef old_map = node_info->possible_maps().at(0);
8510  auto MaybeAliases = [&](compiler::MapRef map) -> bool {
8511  return map.equals(old_map);
8512  };
8513  known_node_aspects.ClearUnstableMapsIfAny(MaybeAliases);
8514  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8515  std::cout << " ! StoreMap: Clearing unstable map "
8516  << Brief(*old_map.object()) << std::endl;
8517  }
8518  return;
8519  }
8520  }
8521  break;
8522  }
8523  }
8524  // TODO(olivf): Only invalidate nodes with the same type.
8525  known_node_aspects.ClearUnstableMaps();
8526  if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8527  std::cout << " ! StoreMap: Clearing unstable maps" << std::endl;
8528  }
8529 }

8552 std::optional<int32_t> NodeBase::TryGetInt32ConstantInput(int index) {
